1
00:01:05,588 --> 00:01:07,453
<i>Taking off at 9.10.</i>

2
00:01:09,492 --> 00:01:12,358
All clear, George.
Watch for the light.

3
00:01:25,205 --> 00:01:29,665
Glendale calling NC95W.
Go ahead.

4
00:01:30,878 --> 00:01:33,972
NC95W answering Glendale.

5
00:01:34,081 --> 00:01:36,242
I'll be in in about
five minutes.

6
00:01:36,350 --> 00:01:37,976
How'd you make out, Loop?

7
00:01:38,084 --> 00:01:39,711
Did you get your passenger
there on time?

8
00:01:39,819 --> 00:01:42,879
I got him there just
in time to see his wife.

9
00:01:42,989 --> 00:01:44,889
Have you seen Shirley
around anywheres?

10
00:01:44,991 --> 00:01:48,051
No, not yet,
but she'll be here.

11
00:01:48,161 --> 00:01:50,628
She always is
when you come in.

12
00:02:18,188 --> 00:02:20,418
Where are you goin'?

13
00:02:20,523 --> 00:02:22,616
I'm going to the airport.

14
00:02:22,725 --> 00:02:24,625
ZJump in.
I'll give you a lift.

15
00:02:24,727 --> 00:02:27,752
Thanks, mister, but I'll
have to get a faster car.

16
00:02:27,863 --> 00:02:29,660
I'm in a hurry.

17
00:02:29,765 --> 00:02:34,259
You're the most particular
hitchhiker I ever saw.

18
00:02:34,369 --> 00:02:36,929
Well, thanks, anyway.

19
00:02:45,680 --> 00:02:47,671
Hello, Shirley.
Goin' to the airport?

20
00:02:47,782 --> 00:02:50,273
Yes, thank you.

21
00:02:50,384 --> 00:02:53,147
Come on, hop in.
That-a girl.

22
00:03:00,961 --> 00:03:02,428
Hello, Loop.

23
00:03:17,642 --> 00:03:21,408
I bet you wish you
were up there with him.

24
00:03:21,513 --> 00:03:23,811
I will be someday.

25
00:03:41,864 --> 00:03:42,922
Contact.

26
00:03:43,032 --> 00:03:44,090
Contact.

27
00:03:44,200 --> 00:03:46,100
Ha ha ha!
Come on.

28
00:03:48,371 --> 00:03:50,168
Contact. Ha ha!

29
00:03:50,273 --> 00:03:51,934
Hiya, Loop.

30
00:03:52,041 --> 00:03:53,872
Hiya, Bill. Check the oil
when you gas it.

31
00:03:53,975 --> 00:03:54,942
Yowzuh.

32
00:03:55,043 --> 00:03:56,772
Come on, honey.
Up you come.

33
00:03:56,878 --> 00:03:57,936
There.

34
00:04:00,482 --> 00:04:02,211
Hello, Shirley.

35
00:04:02,317 --> 00:04:04,877
- Hello, honey. How was it, Loop?
- Hello,Jack.

36
00:04:04,986 --> 00:04:07,283
A little bumpy over the hills.
Are you off again?

37
00:04:07,388 --> 00:04:08,878
Sure. I'll be eating
my Christmas dinner...

38
00:04:08,989 --> 00:04:10,923
in New York tomorrow.
Well, Merry Christmas, Shirley.

39
00:04:11,025 --> 00:04:13,687
Merry Christmas
and lots of tailwind.

40
00:04:13,794 --> 00:04:16,490
- Ha ha ha! Thanks.
- So long.

41
00:04:19,365 --> 00:04:23,096
You wait here, honey.
I'll be right back.

42
00:04:23,203 --> 00:04:25,000
- Hiya, Tony.
- Good morning, sir.

43
00:04:25,104 --> 00:04:26,128
Hello, fellas.

44
00:04:34,546 --> 00:04:36,707
- Tony.
- Yes, missy?

45
00:04:36,815 --> 00:04:39,943
You didn't dust
my daddy's picture.

46
00:04:40,052 --> 00:04:41,451
Here, missy.

47
00:04:44,388 --> 00:04:47,289
You givin' your daddy
a clean face?

48
00:04:47,391 --> 00:04:50,383
Yes. Don't you think
he needs it?

49
00:04:50,494 --> 00:04:52,462
I think you do, too.

50
00:04:52,563 --> 00:04:54,121
Here. Wet.

51
00:04:57,067 --> 00:04:59,968
There you are,
young lady. Come on.

52
00:05:00,070 --> 00:05:01,401
My daddy could fly better...

53
00:05:01,504 --> 00:05:03,404
than anybody in the world,
couldn't he?

54
00:05:03,506 --> 00:05:08,375
That's right- better than
anybody in the whole world.

55
00:05:08,478 --> 00:05:11,412
You know, your daddy
and I were pals...

56
00:05:11,513 --> 00:05:15,415
ever since we were
about as big as you are.

57
00:05:15,517 --> 00:05:17,417
He was my best friend.

58
00:05:17,519 --> 00:05:19,419
That's why I'm your godfather.

59
00:05:19,521 --> 00:05:21,920
And then one day,
he cracked up...

60
00:05:22,023 --> 00:05:24,423
and went away to heaven,
didn't he?

61
00:05:24,525 --> 00:05:25,924
That's right.

62
00:05:26,027 --> 00:05:28,928
I'll bet when I'm a flyer,
I won't crack up.

63
00:05:29,030 --> 00:05:30,930
When you're ready
to be a flyer...

64
00:05:31,032 --> 00:05:33,625
we're gonna buy you
a great big noncrackable ship.

65
00:05:33,734 --> 00:05:35,429
Say, that reminds me.
I found an old scrapbook...

66
00:05:35,535 --> 00:05:37,628
the other day with some pictures
of your daddy and me in it.

67
00:05:37,738 --> 00:05:39,831
- Would you like to see it?
- Oh, yes!

68
00:05:39,940 --> 00:05:41,032
I'll get it.

69
00:05:43,777 --> 00:05:46,939
- Hi, Harry. Grab some of these, will you?
- Sure.

70
00:05:47,046 --> 00:05:48,274
Hello, honey.

71
00:05:48,381 --> 00:05:49,814
Hello, little boy.

72
00:05:49,915 --> 00:05:51,940
I'm not a little boy.
I'm a little girl.

73
00:05:52,051 --> 00:05:53,609
Are you sure?

74
00:05:53,719 --> 00:05:55,243
Yes, I'm sure.

75
00:05:55,354 --> 00:05:57,652
Well, I just didn't
want to take any chances.

76
00:05:59,557 --> 00:06:01,582
Now, that's mistletoe.
And when you hold it...

77
00:06:01,693 --> 00:06:03,684
over anybody's head,
you can kiss them.

78
00:06:03,795 --> 00:06:05,194
Beat it, you chiseler.

79
00:06:05,297 --> 00:06:06,423
OK, kid.

80
00:06:06,531 --> 00:06:07,725
Move over.

81
00:06:15,239 --> 00:06:16,638
There's your daddy
on the day...

82
00:06:16,740 --> 00:06:18,401
he broke
the transcontinental record.

83
00:06:21,111 --> 00:06:25,012
And there's your daddy and me
when we first got our wings.

84
00:06:27,617 --> 00:06:30,586
We'll skip that.

85
00:06:30,687 --> 00:06:32,587
Wait a minute.
There ought to be...

86
00:06:32,689 --> 00:06:34,088
another one
in here someplace.

87
00:06:34,190 --> 00:06:35,680
Who's that?

88
00:06:39,261 --> 00:06:41,957
A girl I used to know.

89
00:06:42,064 --> 00:06:43,964
She's a pretty lady.

90
00:06:44,066 --> 00:06:46,967
I used to think so.

91
00:06:47,069 --> 00:06:49,969
But it's not enough
to be pretty here.

92
00:06:50,071 --> 00:06:53,472
You've got to be
pretty in here, too.

93
00:06:53,574 --> 00:06:57,476
How can you be
pretty in there?

94
00:06:57,578 --> 00:06:59,808
By thinking
the right thoughts...

95
00:06:59,914 --> 00:07:02,040
and doing
the right things...

96
00:07:02,148 --> 00:07:05,049
and eating plenty
of spinach. Ha ha ha!

97
00:07:05,151 --> 00:07:07,551
Say, we better call up
your mother...

98
00:07:07,654 --> 00:07:09,554
before she starts
to worry about you.

99
00:07:09,656 --> 00:07:13,887
She won't worry
as long as I'm with you.

100
00:07:13,992 --> 00:07:15,892
Fledrich 4230.

101
00:07:24,169 --> 00:07:25,397
Good heavens.

102
00:07:25,504 --> 00:07:27,903
Will no one
answer the phone?

103
00:07:28,005 --> 00:07:29,097
Hello.

104
00:07:29,207 --> 00:07:31,437
May I please speak
to Mrs. Blake?

105
00:07:31,542 --> 00:07:33,737
Mary.

106
00:07:33,845 --> 00:07:34,903
Mary.

107
00:07:35,012 --> 00:07:36,274
Yes, ma'am?

108
00:07:36,381 --> 00:07:38,008
The telephone- for you.

109
00:07:41,518 --> 00:07:43,179
Thank you.

110
00:07:43,286 --> 00:07:44,275
Hello?

111
00:07:44,388 --> 00:07:46,083
This is Loop.

112
00:07:46,189 --> 00:07:49,420
I just wanted you to know
that Shirley's with me.

113
00:07:49,526 --> 00:07:50,924
Hello, Mother.

114
00:07:51,026 --> 00:07:53,790
I'll have one of the boys
drive her home later.

115
00:07:53,896 --> 00:07:56,091
All right, Loop.
Thanks.

116
00:07:57,633 --> 00:07:58,691
Mary.

117
00:07:58,801 --> 00:07:59,768
Yes, ma'am?

118
00:08:01,470 --> 00:08:04,370
I don't approve of all
these telephone calls.

119
00:08:04,472 --> 00:08:05,871
I'm sorry.

120
00:08:05,974 --> 00:08:07,942
And I don't approve
of all these aviators...

121
00:08:08,042 --> 00:08:09,907
who keep coming here
to see your little girl.

122
00:08:10,011 --> 00:08:13,378
She's sort of a pet with them.
They all knew her father.

123
00:08:13,481 --> 00:08:16,381
I know that,
but I really can't have it.

124
00:08:16,483 --> 00:08:18,576
You know it isn't everyone
who'd engage a maid...

125
00:08:18,685 --> 00:08:19,879
with a small child.

126
00:08:19,987 --> 00:08:22,455
I have no fault to find
with your work...

127
00:08:22,556 --> 00:08:24,421
but if you want
to stay on with us...

128
00:08:24,525 --> 00:08:26,049
you'll have to
correct these things.

129
00:08:26,160 --> 00:08:27,889
Yes, ma'am, I will.

130
00:08:27,995 --> 00:08:29,689
Very well.

131
00:08:33,533 --> 00:08:35,296
I told you
when you engaged her...

132
00:08:35,401 --> 00:08:36,834
that it wouldn't work out.

133
00:08:36,936 --> 00:08:38,836
Well, she was so pathetic
about wanting a nice home...

134
00:08:38,938 --> 00:08:40,428
for her little girl...

135
00:08:40,540 --> 00:08:42,507
that I let my sympathy get
the better of my judgment.

136
00:08:42,607 --> 00:08:44,837
I'll let her go
right after the holidays.

137
00:08:44,943 --> 00:08:46,069
Hmm. Fine.

138
00:08:52,851 --> 00:08:54,909
Ah. Through with
the upstairs already?

139
00:08:55,019 --> 00:08:56,077
Yes.

140
00:08:57,188 --> 00:08:59,247
What's wrong, dearie?

141
00:08:59,356 --> 00:09:02,348
Mrs. Smythe doesn't want me to
have any more telephone calls.

142
00:09:02,460 --> 00:09:04,860
She don't? Well, well, now,
ain't that too bad.

143
00:09:04,962 --> 00:09:07,794
Ha! Her and
her highfalutin ways...

144
00:09:07,897 --> 00:09:10,365
and him that finicky.
They both give me a pain.

145
00:09:10,467 --> 00:09:12,367
Tut tut, Elizabeth.
I shall not stand here...

146
00:09:12,469 --> 00:09:15,302
and listen to you
defame our employers.

147
00:09:15,405 --> 00:09:16,702
What?

148
00:09:16,806 --> 00:09:19,865
Besides, I have to go
down to the post office.

149
00:09:19,975 --> 00:09:21,203
Ha ha ha!

150
00:09:21,310 --> 00:09:24,006
Don't forget
to pick up those things.

151
00:09:24,112 --> 00:09:26,273
What things, my love?

152
00:09:26,381 --> 00:09:28,781
Don't you remember?
The things I told you to get?

153
00:09:34,989 --> 00:09:36,456
Oh, you fool, you.

154
00:09:36,557 --> 00:09:39,287
The sewin' kit I told you
to get for Shirley.

155
00:09:39,393 --> 00:09:41,384
Oh, right.

156
00:09:43,597 --> 00:09:46,566
I wanted it to be a surprise.

157
00:09:46,666 --> 00:09:49,066
I guess it won't matter
if you know.

158
00:09:49,169 --> 00:09:50,568
ZJust a bit
of a Christmas gift.

159
00:09:50,670 --> 00:09:51,568
You're awfully kind.

160
00:09:51,671 --> 00:09:53,195
Aw, go on.

161
00:09:53,306 --> 00:09:56,069
I bought a few things for her.
Not very much, of course.

162
00:09:56,175 --> 00:09:59,076
It was different
when her father was alive.

163
00:09:59,178 --> 00:10:01,078
Oh, yes, the poor young fellow.

164
00:10:01,180 --> 00:10:02,670
Well, it must be
a comfort to know...

165
00:10:02,781 --> 00:10:04,248
you're doin' the best
you can for the little one.

166
00:10:04,350 --> 00:10:06,250
She's a sweet child.

167
00:10:06,352 --> 00:10:09,252
Not like that young one of theirs.

168
00:10:09,354 --> 00:10:11,822
There's a brat if ever one lived.

169
00:10:13,324 --> 00:10:15,019
Now, darling,
don't get yourself all excited.

170
00:10:15,126 --> 00:10:18,027
Child: I don't care! No! No!

171
00:10:18,162 --> 00:10:19,390
No! No! No!

172
00:10:19,497 --> 00:10:21,657
Darling, you must practice
your piano lesson.

173
00:10:21,765 --> 00:10:23,426
You won't have to
practice again...

174
00:10:23,534 --> 00:10:25,092
until after Santa Claus
has been here.

175
00:10:25,202 --> 00:10:27,033
There ain't any Santa Claus!

176
00:10:27,137 --> 00:10:29,367
Don't say "ain't," darling. Say "isn't. "

177
00:10:29,473 --> 00:10:31,498
Ain't! Ain't! Ain't!

178
00:10:31,608 --> 00:10:33,768
What's all this noise about?

179
00:10:33,876 --> 00:10:37,277
Mother wants me to practice,
and I don't wanna!

180
00:10:37,380 --> 00:10:39,177
You must do
as Mama says, dear.

181
00:10:39,282 --> 00:10:40,271
Well, I ain't gonna!

182
00:10:40,383 --> 00:10:41,941
Now, look here,
young woman-

183
00:10:42,051 --> 00:10:43,951
Remember what
the psychoanalyst said-

184
00:10:44,053 --> 00:10:46,452
The child mind must
never be coerced.

185
00:10:46,555 --> 00:10:49,456
One must use
persuasion and reason.

186
00:10:49,558 --> 00:10:51,355
Now, darling...

187
00:10:51,459 --> 00:10:55,293
practice your lesson, and mama
will buy you something nice.

188
00:10:55,397 --> 00:10:56,455
What?

189
00:10:56,565 --> 00:10:58,862
- Anything you like.
- Anything?

190
00:10:58,966 --> 00:11:01,059
Yes, dear. What would you
especially like?

191
00:11:01,168 --> 00:11:05,537
A machine gun!
Rat-a-tat! Rat-a-tat!

192
00:11:05,639 --> 00:11:08,437
Rat-a-tat! Rat-a-tat!
Rat-a-tat!

193
00:11:14,847 --> 00:11:16,781
That's a good girl.

194
00:11:20,353 --> 00:11:22,446
? 1, 2, 3, 1, 2, 3?

195
00:11:22,555 --> 00:11:23,816
? 1, 2, 3, 1?

196
00:11:25,190 --> 00:11:28,091
? 1, 2, 3, 1, 2, 3...?

197
00:11:28,193 --> 00:11:32,129
Hey! Is there anybody at all
in this confounded house?

198
00:11:33,865 --> 00:11:35,764
? 1, 2, 3, 1, 2, 3?

199
00:11:35,866 --> 00:11:37,629
? 1, 2, 3, 1?

200
00:11:37,735 --> 00:11:40,761
Hey! Somebody! Anybody!

201
00:11:40,871 --> 00:11:44,602
Come and help me downstairs!

202
00:11:44,709 --> 00:11:45,767
Hey!

203
00:11:45,876 --> 00:11:47,775
? 1, 2, 3, 1, 2, 3?

204
00:11:47,877 --> 00:11:50,675
So you think you're gonna make
me stay up here today, do you?

205
00:11:50,780 --> 00:11:52,577
Well, I'll show you.

206
00:11:52,682 --> 00:11:54,809
? 1, 2, 3, 1, 2, 3, 4?

207
00:12:01,190 --> 00:12:02,088
Oh!

208
00:12:02,191 --> 00:12:03,522
Doggone it!

209
00:12:07,696 --> 00:12:09,095
Why, Uncle Ned!

210
00:12:09,198 --> 00:12:10,756
Why didn't you call us?

211
00:12:10,866 --> 00:12:12,265
Call you?

212
00:12:12,368 --> 00:12:15,268
I yelled, and I shouted
and bellowed.

213
00:12:15,370 --> 00:12:16,598
A fat lot of good it did me.

214
00:12:16,704 --> 00:12:18,831
No one pays
any attention to me.

215
00:12:18,940 --> 00:12:21,272
No one cares
what happens to me.

216
00:12:21,376 --> 00:12:23,276
All you do is think of yourselves.

217
00:12:23,378 --> 00:12:24,936
Oh, Uncle Ned,
you know that isn't so.

218
00:12:25,045 --> 00:12:26,103
Mary.

219
00:12:26,213 --> 00:12:28,113
Yes, Mr. Smythe?

220
00:12:28,215 --> 00:12:31,116
My name is Smith!
His name is Smythe.

221
00:12:31,218 --> 00:12:32,776
Yes, Mr. Smith.

222
00:12:32,886 --> 00:12:34,786
Didn't you hear me holler
a little while ago?

223
00:12:34,888 --> 00:12:36,788
No, sir, I didn't.

224
00:12:36,890 --> 00:12:39,289
Folks around here had
better get their ears fixed.

225
00:12:39,392 --> 00:12:40,518
That's all, Mary.

226
00:12:40,626 --> 00:12:42,787
? 1 and 2 and 3 and?

227
00:12:42,895 --> 00:12:45,455
? 1 and 2 and 3 and?

228
00:12:45,564 --> 00:12:47,464
? 1 and 2 and 3 and?

229
00:12:47,566 --> 00:12:49,466
? 1 and 2 and 3 and...
1 and 2 and-?

230
00:12:49,568 --> 00:12:50,966
Stop it!

231
00:12:51,069 --> 00:12:52,969
? 1 and 2 and 3 and?

232
00:12:53,071 --> 00:12:55,130
Is that all you know?

233
00:12:55,240 --> 00:12:56,298
Mama! Mama!

234
00:12:56,408 --> 00:12:58,239
Mama. Mama.

235
00:12:58,343 --> 00:13:00,311
It's a good thing
I'm not your mama.

236
00:13:00,412 --> 00:13:02,402
Why, it's enough
to drive a man crazy.

237
00:13:02,513 --> 00:13:04,242
Things better be a little
different around here...

238
00:13:04,348 --> 00:13:07,215
or you're gonna see
the last of me.

239
00:13:09,319 --> 00:13:11,048
And another thing-

240
00:13:11,155 --> 00:13:12,554
You stop telling people...

241
00:13:12,656 --> 00:13:15,215
I made my money
in sanitary engineering.

242
00:13:15,324 --> 00:13:17,224
It was sewers!

243
00:13:17,326 --> 00:13:20,227
Sewers! And don't you forget it!

244
00:13:24,333 --> 00:13:26,233
And, oh...

245
00:13:29,838 --> 00:13:32,739
How much longer
must I stand this?

246
00:13:32,841 --> 00:13:34,741
Now, now, dear. Be calm.

247
00:13:34,843 --> 00:13:36,743
That horrid man.
He's just impossible.

248
00:13:36,845 --> 00:13:38,369
Yes, I know he's trying,
but after all...

249
00:13:38,480 --> 00:13:40,743
we can afford to be patient.
It will pay us in the end.

250
00:13:40,848 --> 00:13:43,248
Any money he leaves us
we'll have earned.

251
00:13:43,350 --> 00:13:44,749
Yes, that's true...

252
00:13:44,852 --> 00:13:46,444
but with my business
in such condition...

253
00:13:46,554 --> 00:13:48,454
we'd better keep on
humoring him.

254
00:13:48,556 --> 00:13:51,616
And, Mama, every time
he sees me, he makes a face.

255
00:13:51,726 --> 00:13:53,522
Never mind, darling.

256
00:13:53,626 --> 00:13:55,355
Well, I must be getting
down to the office.

257
00:13:55,462 --> 00:13:57,089
- Good-bye, dear.
- Good-bye.

258
00:13:57,197 --> 00:13:58,755
Good-bye, darling.

259
00:14:01,301 --> 00:14:03,201
Never you mind, darling.

260
00:14:03,303 --> 00:14:05,702
Don't you let him worry you.

261
00:14:05,804 --> 00:14:07,704
Sit up.
Sit up.

262
00:14:07,806 --> 00:14:09,706
- Ha ha ha!
- Ha ha ha!

263
00:14:09,808 --> 00:14:12,208
Miss Blake's car is ready, sir.

264
00:14:12,311 --> 00:14:13,869
Very good, Meadows.

265
00:14:13,979 --> 00:14:15,879
The royal chariot awaits, madam.

266
00:14:15,981 --> 00:14:16,879
Come on.

267
00:14:16,982 --> 00:14:17,879
Ha ha ha!

268
00:14:17,982 --> 00:14:19,381
Bye, Ray.

269
00:14:19,484 --> 00:14:21,384
I'll see you later.

270
00:14:21,486 --> 00:14:23,681
Bye, honey. Bye.

271
00:14:24,822 --> 00:14:26,221
Hello, Harry.

272
00:14:26,324 --> 00:14:27,723
Hello, Shirley.

273
00:14:27,825 --> 00:14:29,383
Hi, Shirley.

274
00:14:29,494 --> 00:14:30,391
Hi.

275
00:14:30,494 --> 00:14:31,859
Hello there.

276
00:14:46,842 --> 00:14:48,400
Mr. Higgins?

277
00:14:48,511 --> 00:14:50,240
Yes, madam?

278
00:14:50,346 --> 00:14:52,746
See that?
That's mistletoe.

279
00:14:56,684 --> 00:14:58,242
Thank you, madam.

280
00:14:59,687 --> 00:15:01,678
- Mother.
- Yes, darling?

281
00:15:01,790 --> 00:15:03,690
May I help you
with the dishes?

282
00:15:03,792 --> 00:15:06,590
No, honey, but I tell
you what you can do.

283
00:15:06,694 --> 00:15:07,751
Take this down
to the incinerator...

284
00:15:07,861 --> 00:15:09,192
and leave it there.

285
00:15:09,296 --> 00:15:10,194
All right.

286
00:15:14,802 --> 00:15:17,202
Higgins, what's that
on your face?

287
00:15:17,304 --> 00:15:18,703
My face, madam?

288
00:15:18,806 --> 00:15:19,829
Yes.

289
00:15:22,708 --> 00:15:25,108
It appears to be
chocolate, madam.

290
00:15:37,756 --> 00:15:39,519
Look out for the police car!

291
00:15:48,766 --> 00:15:50,666
Here comes the police car!

292
00:15:50,768 --> 00:15:53,100
Everybody, get out of the way!

293
00:15:54,405 --> 00:15:55,702
Everybody, get out of the way!

294
00:15:55,806 --> 00:15:57,466
Bang! Bang! Bang!
Bang! Bang!

295
00:16:10,252 --> 00:16:13,153
Why, you poor little thing.

296
00:16:13,255 --> 00:16:15,155
You must have cracked up.

297
00:16:15,257 --> 00:16:17,782
You should be in the hospital.

298
00:16:22,763 --> 00:16:24,663
Hey, that's my doll.

299
00:16:24,765 --> 00:16:28,667
Well, I just found her here.

300
00:16:28,769 --> 00:16:30,669
You can't have her.

301
00:16:30,771 --> 00:16:32,671
You bad old thing.
You ran away from home...

302
00:16:32,773 --> 00:16:34,672
and I'm gonna spank you.

303
00:16:34,774 --> 00:16:37,174
If you give her to me...

304
00:16:37,277 --> 00:16:39,609
I'll take care of her.
I'll wash her face...

305
00:16:39,713 --> 00:16:42,181
and make her some
clothes and everything.

306
00:16:42,282 --> 00:16:45,183
You can't have her!
You wanna know why?

307
00:16:45,285 --> 00:16:47,149
Because I'm gonna kill her.

308
00:16:50,122 --> 00:16:52,454
? Happy, happy, happy days?

309
00:16:52,558 --> 00:16:54,685
? Happy days, happy days?

310
00:16:54,793 --> 00:16:57,023
? Happy days, happy days?

311
00:16:57,129 --> 00:16:58,926
? Happy days, happy-?

312
00:17:01,299 --> 00:17:04,029
Hey, what are you gonna
get for Christmas?

313
00:17:04,135 --> 00:17:07,366
I'm gonna get a doll house
with real furniture...

314
00:17:07,472 --> 00:17:09,372
and a little piano
and a tennis racket...

315
00:17:09,474 --> 00:17:10,736
and a great big doll.

316
00:17:10,842 --> 00:17:13,401
I asked Santy Claus
to bring me a doll.

317
00:17:13,510 --> 00:17:15,375
Santa Claus? Pooh!

318
00:17:15,479 --> 00:17:17,447
There ain't any Santa Claus.

319
00:17:17,547 --> 00:17:19,572
- There is, too.
- There is not!

320
00:17:19,683 --> 00:17:22,709
There is not, because
my psychoanalyst told me.

321
00:17:22,819 --> 00:17:24,718
There ain't any Santa Claus.

322
00:17:24,820 --> 00:17:27,050
There ain't any fairies
or giants or anything like that.

323
00:17:27,156 --> 00:17:29,215
I'll bet you'd feel bad...

324
00:17:29,325 --> 00:17:30,724
if you woke up
tomorrow morning...

325
00:17:30,826 --> 00:17:32,384
and you didn't
have any presents.

326
00:17:32,495 --> 00:17:35,055
Well, I won't.
You want to know why?

327
00:17:35,164 --> 00:17:38,223
'Cause I already peeked
in the closet and saw 'em.

328
00:17:38,333 --> 00:17:42,269
I don't care what you saw.
There is a Santy Claus.

329
00:17:42,370 --> 00:17:43,632
There ain't!

330
00:17:48,243 --> 00:17:49,470
Mr. Smith?

331
00:17:49,576 --> 00:17:50,668
Huh?

332
00:17:50,778 --> 00:17:53,144
There is a Santy Claus, isn't there?

333
00:17:53,247 --> 00:17:54,976
What did she say?

334
00:17:55,082 --> 00:17:56,913
She says there isn't.

335
00:17:57,017 --> 00:17:58,416
Then there is.

336
00:17:58,519 --> 00:18:01,578
You think you're smart, don't you?

337
00:18:01,688 --> 00:18:04,589
Well, I'll show you!

338
00:18:04,691 --> 00:18:06,591
You'll what?

339
00:18:06,693 --> 00:18:07,921
You'll...

340
00:18:11,631 --> 00:18:13,360
Aarrrgh!

341
00:18:13,466 --> 00:18:16,366
Get outta here!

342
00:18:16,468 --> 00:18:18,936
Go on!
Get out of here!

343
00:18:19,037 --> 00:18:21,437
Go on! Get outta here!

344
00:18:21,540 --> 00:18:23,667
Mama! Mama!
Mama!

345
00:18:23,775 --> 00:18:25,174
Mama!

346
00:18:25,277 --> 00:18:26,675
Shirley.

347
00:18:28,779 --> 00:18:31,680
Shirley, where are you?

348
00:18:33,284 --> 00:18:35,184
Here I am.

349
00:18:35,286 --> 00:18:37,982
Oh, well, my goodness.

350
00:18:44,794 --> 00:18:46,694
We got rid of her, all right.

351
00:18:46,796 --> 00:18:48,354
Thanks, Mr. Smith.

352
00:18:48,465 --> 00:18:50,365
Oh, that's all right.

353
00:18:55,304 --> 00:18:57,704
I like you.

354
00:18:57,806 --> 00:19:01,139
You're the only one
around here that does.

355
00:19:01,243 --> 00:19:02,642
They don't like me...

356
00:19:02,745 --> 00:19:07,147
and listen,
I don't like them, either.

357
00:19:14,655 --> 00:19:15,986
I made the arrangements...

358
00:19:16,090 --> 00:19:17,556
and everything's
all set for tomorrow.

359
00:19:17,657 --> 00:19:18,988
It's wonderful
of you and the boys...

360
00:19:19,092 --> 00:19:21,492
to give Shirley
her Christmas party.

361
00:19:21,595 --> 00:19:23,426
Oh, we're getting a big kick
out of it ourselves.

362
00:19:23,530 --> 00:19:24,656
She'll be so surprised.

363
00:19:24,765 --> 00:19:26,357
She doesn't expect much, you know.

364
00:19:26,466 --> 00:19:27,660
Now, get her down to the airport...

365
00:19:27,768 --> 00:19:28,927
as early in the morning as you can.

366
00:19:29,035 --> 00:19:30,400
I may not be able
to come with her...

367
00:19:30,503 --> 00:19:32,232
but I'll be down just
as soon as I can get away.

368
00:19:32,338 --> 00:19:33,430
That'll be fine.

369
00:19:33,539 --> 00:19:35,507
Hello, Mr. Merritt.
Merry Christmas.

370
00:19:35,608 --> 00:19:37,337
The same to you.

371
00:19:37,443 --> 00:19:39,070
I'm just after making
myself a cup of tea.

372
00:19:39,178 --> 00:19:40,873
- Will you have one?
- Sure.

373
00:19:40,980 --> 00:19:42,003
Ah, fine.

374
00:19:42,113 --> 00:19:43,671
Hello, Loop.

375
00:19:43,782 --> 00:19:45,682
Hiya, honey.
All ready for Christmas?

376
00:19:45,784 --> 00:19:48,685
I've been ready
for a long time.

377
00:19:48,787 --> 00:19:50,186
Hello, Loop.

378
00:19:50,288 --> 00:19:51,687
Hiya, Thomas.

379
00:19:51,790 --> 00:19:53,189
All ready!

380
00:19:53,291 --> 00:19:54,723
Come on.

381
00:19:54,825 --> 00:19:58,727
Yes, dear, I think Friday
will be all right.

382
00:19:58,829 --> 00:20:01,229
That will be fine.

383
00:20:01,331 --> 00:20:04,732
Very well. We'll make it
definite, then.

384
00:20:04,835 --> 00:20:06,631
Thank you so much
for inviting us.

385
00:20:06,736 --> 00:20:07,998
Good-bye, dear.

386
00:20:10,373 --> 00:20:12,102
This is good cake.

387
00:20:12,208 --> 00:20:14,108
It ought to be.
I whipped it up myself.

388
00:20:14,210 --> 00:20:15,802
How are you,
Mr. Merritt?

389
00:20:15,912 --> 00:20:17,607
The compliments
of the season to you.

390
00:20:17,713 --> 00:20:19,612
Same to you,
Mr. Higgins.

391
00:20:19,714 --> 00:20:22,615
The cup that cheers
but not inebriates.

392
00:20:22,717 --> 00:20:24,116
Ha ha ha!

393
00:20:24,219 --> 00:20:26,119
Wow! That's hot.

394
00:20:26,221 --> 00:20:28,121
- Ha ha ha!
- Ha ha ha!

395
00:20:28,223 --> 00:20:29,451
Higgins.

396
00:20:29,558 --> 00:20:31,150
Yes, madam?

397
00:20:32,726 --> 00:20:34,956
My cousin's arriving
from New York tomorrow...

398
00:20:35,062 --> 00:20:36,461
and I want you to be sure...

399
00:20:36,564 --> 00:20:38,122
that everything
is done just right.

400
00:20:38,232 --> 00:20:39,995
Yes, madam.

401
00:20:40,101 --> 00:20:42,934
- Thomas, you will meet the plane in the morning.
- Yes, ma'am.

402
00:20:43,037 --> 00:20:45,061
I'm very anxious to show her
that we can do things...

403
00:20:45,171 --> 00:20:48,607
exactly as well out here
as they do in the East.

404
00:20:48,708 --> 00:20:51,802
I want perfect meals
and perfect service.

405
00:20:51,911 --> 00:20:53,003
Is that understood?

406
00:20:53,113 --> 00:20:54,410
Yes, ma'am.

407
00:20:54,514 --> 00:20:56,105
- And, Mary...
- Yes, ma'am?

408
00:20:56,215 --> 00:20:57,944
I hope you'll remember
what I told you...

409
00:20:58,050 --> 00:21:00,518
this morning...
about visitors?

410
00:21:00,619 --> 00:21:02,348
Yes, ma'am.

411
00:21:05,757 --> 00:21:10,022
And I don't want to
have to remind you again.

412
00:21:11,262 --> 00:21:13,162
Remember that,
Mrs. Higgins-

413
00:21:13,264 --> 00:21:15,164
Anything else than perfection...

414
00:21:15,266 --> 00:21:18,667
and, ggkktt...
off goes your head.

415
00:21:18,769 --> 00:21:20,498
My head, indeed.

416
00:21:20,605 --> 00:21:23,164
You better look
after your own.

417
00:21:27,110 --> 00:21:29,203
How can you stand working
for people like that?

418
00:21:29,312 --> 00:21:31,542
Oh, I don't mind.
Could be worse.

419
00:21:31,648 --> 00:21:34,241
Well, I guess you know
your own business best.

420
00:21:35,451 --> 00:21:38,215
Now we'll have a little pepper.

421
00:21:38,320 --> 00:21:40,049
Good-bye, Mrs. Higgins.

422
00:21:44,326 --> 00:21:46,054
Ah-choo!

423
00:21:46,161 --> 00:21:47,890
I'll see you tomorrow.

424
00:21:47,996 --> 00:21:49,224
OK, Loop.

425
00:22:04,778 --> 00:22:06,678
Hello, dear.

426
00:22:06,780 --> 00:22:08,680
Mother, I undressed myself.

427
00:22:08,782 --> 00:22:12,182
I put my clothes away-
all folded and everything.

428
00:22:12,285 --> 00:22:13,809
Well, you're mother's
precious little angel...

429
00:22:13,920 --> 00:22:15,410
that's what you are.

430
00:22:15,521 --> 00:22:19,013
No, I'm not,
because angels have wings...

431
00:22:19,125 --> 00:22:20,717
like these.

432
00:22:21,761 --> 00:22:23,990
Those are your daddy's wings.

433
00:22:24,095 --> 00:22:27,997
I know, and he's really
an angel, isn't he?

434
00:22:28,099 --> 00:22:29,498
Yes, darling.

435
00:22:35,273 --> 00:22:38,673
Now, then. Are you all ready
to hang up your stocking?

436
00:22:40,778 --> 00:22:43,178
- Mother.
- Yes, dear?

437
00:22:43,280 --> 00:22:45,077
You know,
I was thinking today...

438
00:22:45,182 --> 00:22:47,514
- about hanging up my stocking...
- Yes?

439
00:22:47,618 --> 00:22:49,016
and I thought maybe...

440
00:22:49,118 --> 00:22:51,848
if Santa brought me
a great big present-

441
00:22:51,955 --> 00:22:55,049
of course, he mightn't-
but then if he did-

442
00:22:55,158 --> 00:22:56,455
Yes, if he did?

443
00:22:56,559 --> 00:22:59,687
Well, you know, my stockings
are awful little.

444
00:22:59,796 --> 00:23:03,595
I know. And you want mother
to lend you one of hers.

445
00:23:03,699 --> 00:23:07,692
Oh, no. I already borrowed
one of Mrs. Higgins'.

446
00:23:07,803 --> 00:23:10,499
Oh, you did?
Ha ha ha!

447
00:23:13,808 --> 00:23:16,709
See? It's a real good, big one.

448
00:23:16,811 --> 00:23:19,575
Santa Claus could get
most anything in that.

449
00:23:19,680 --> 00:23:22,114
Shall we hang it here?

450
00:23:24,318 --> 00:23:27,218
Will it hold everything
without falling down?

451
00:23:27,320 --> 00:23:29,220
I think it will.

452
00:23:29,322 --> 00:23:31,119
Now... say your prayers.

453
00:23:31,224 --> 00:23:32,486
Then mother
will tuck you in...

454
00:23:32,592 --> 00:23:34,822
you'll close your eyes
and go to sleep...

455
00:23:34,928 --> 00:23:36,122
and then-

456
00:23:36,229 --> 00:23:37,958
And then it will
be Christmas.

457
00:23:38,064 --> 00:23:41,927
That's right.
Now, there you are.

458
00:23:46,038 --> 00:23:49,735
Dear Lord, please bless
my mother and me...

459
00:23:49,842 --> 00:23:52,742
and Loop
and all of the aviators...

460
00:23:52,844 --> 00:23:55,244
and Mr. and Mrs. Higgins...

461
00:23:55,346 --> 00:23:59,248
and Mr. and Mrs. Smythe
and Mr. Smith-

462
00:24:00,752 --> 00:24:04,152
Do I have to ask him
to bless Joy, too?

463
00:24:04,254 --> 00:24:05,812
Yes, dear.

464
00:24:05,922 --> 00:24:07,651
And bless Joy, too...

465
00:24:07,758 --> 00:24:11,091
and make her a good girl.

466
00:24:11,194 --> 00:24:13,162
- Mother.
- What, dear?

467
00:24:13,263 --> 00:24:15,493
On account of
this is Christmas Eve...

468
00:24:15,598 --> 00:24:17,190
do you think
it will be all right...

469
00:24:17,300 --> 00:24:19,131
if I ask something special?

470
00:24:19,235 --> 00:24:21,760
I'm sure it will.

471
00:24:23,239 --> 00:24:27,141
Dear Lord,
please see my daddy...

472
00:24:27,243 --> 00:24:31,645
and wish him a merry Christmas
from my mother and me...

473
00:24:31,746 --> 00:24:34,146
and tell him we love him...

474
00:24:34,249 --> 00:24:37,912
forever and ever. Amen.

475
00:24:39,754 --> 00:24:42,153
Mother, do you think he will?

476
00:24:42,256 --> 00:24:45,157
I think on this night
of all nights...

477
00:24:45,259 --> 00:24:48,660
God will listen to
the prayer of a child.

478
00:24:48,762 --> 00:24:50,662
Don't cry, Mother.

479
00:24:50,764 --> 00:24:53,664
I get lonesome for him
sometimes, darling.

480
00:24:53,766 --> 00:24:56,667
Don't be lonesome, mother.
You have me.

481
00:24:56,769 --> 00:24:59,704
Yes, my own sweet baby.

482
00:25:01,641 --> 00:25:03,302
And we're together...

483
00:25:03,409 --> 00:25:05,467
and tomorrow's Christmas
and everything.

484
00:25:05,577 --> 00:25:07,204
And it'll be a merry
Christmas, won't it?

485
00:25:07,312 --> 00:25:09,143
The merriest we've ever had.

486
00:25:09,247 --> 00:25:11,147
The very, very merriest.

487
00:25:11,249 --> 00:25:12,477
All right.

488
00:25:12,584 --> 00:25:15,382
Beddy-bye.
In you go.

489
00:25:15,487 --> 00:25:18,148
1, 2, 3!

490
00:25:18,255 --> 00:25:20,655
<i>There you are-
nice and comfy.</i>

491
00:25:20,758 --> 00:25:23,659
Tell me again about
the first Christmas.

492
00:25:23,761 --> 00:25:25,661
All right.

493
00:25:25,763 --> 00:25:29,164
A long, long time ago...

494
00:25:29,266 --> 00:25:32,166
three travelers came to an inn.

495
00:25:32,268 --> 00:25:34,668
And they needed
food and shelter.

496
00:25:34,771 --> 00:25:38,172
Yes, but there was no room
for them in the inn.

497
00:25:38,274 --> 00:25:41,004
And the only place
they could find to sleep...

498
00:25:41,111 --> 00:25:42,941
was in the stable.

499
00:25:43,045 --> 00:25:47,106
In the straw... with the cows.

500
00:25:47,216 --> 00:25:50,185
And there was born that night...

501
00:25:50,285 --> 00:25:53,652
a little baby boy.

502
00:26:11,705 --> 00:26:13,605
Isn't it beautiful, dear?

503
00:26:15,208 --> 00:26:17,608
Merry Christmas, Uncle Ned.

504
00:26:17,711 --> 00:26:18,769
Ohhh...

505
00:26:20,713 --> 00:26:22,908
Oh, look, darling.

506
00:26:23,015 --> 00:26:25,313
Look, darling. Isn't she nice?

507
00:26:25,418 --> 00:26:28,080
I don't want any old doll!

508
00:26:28,187 --> 00:26:30,621
I wanted a wheelchair like his!

509
00:26:31,957 --> 00:26:33,753
Little girls don't
have wheelchairs...

510
00:26:33,858 --> 00:26:36,759
but you have lots of other
nice things to play with.

511
00:26:36,861 --> 00:26:38,761
I don't want
anything else!

512
00:26:38,863 --> 00:26:40,763
I want a wheelchair!

513
00:26:40,865 --> 00:26:42,093
Ohh...

514
00:26:46,403 --> 00:26:48,428
Look, Mrs. Higgins!

515
00:26:48,539 --> 00:26:50,439
Look what Santy Claus
brought me!

516
00:26:50,541 --> 00:26:51,599
Oh, my! My!

517
00:26:51,708 --> 00:26:53,266
Isn't she pretty?
What's her name?

518
00:26:53,377 --> 00:26:55,345
Her name is Mary Lou...

519
00:26:55,446 --> 00:26:57,414
and Santy Claus brought me...

520
00:26:57,514 --> 00:27:00,414
a little man that dances
when you wind him up...

521
