00:41:40,025 --> 00:41:41,424
just you and I.

789
00:41:41,526 --> 00:41:43,425
You mean way up high?

790
00:41:43,527 --> 00:41:44,425
Yep...

791
00:41:44,528 --> 00:41:45,927
way up high.

792
00:41:46,030 --> 00:41:47,395
Come on.

793
00:42:28,970 --> 00:42:30,870
Ooh! We're going up!

794
00:42:30,972 --> 00:42:32,371
That's right.

795
00:42:32,473 --> 00:42:34,440
We're going way up.

796
00:42:35,976 --> 00:42:38,376
Do you know
where we're going?

797
00:42:38,478 --> 00:42:39,877
No.

798
00:42:39,980 --> 00:42:42,380
We're goin'
right up to heaven.

799
00:42:42,482 --> 00:42:44,916
- We are?
- Mm-hmm.

800
00:42:53,993 --> 00:42:55,426
You know, Shirley...

801
00:42:56,996 --> 00:42:58,895
heaven's
a very nice place.

802
00:42:58,997 --> 00:43:02,364
If we're good,
we'll all live there someday.

803
00:43:02,467 --> 00:43:04,367
Yes, I know.

804
00:43:04,469 --> 00:43:07,370
My mother and father
are there now.

805
00:43:07,472 --> 00:43:09,337
So is my daddy.

806
00:43:14,978 --> 00:43:16,878
We're up pretty high now.

807
00:43:16,980 --> 00:43:18,880
Are we getting near it?

808
00:43:18,982 --> 00:43:20,882
We're right in it now.

809
00:43:20,984 --> 00:43:23,816
It's all around us,
everyplace you look.

810
00:43:29,225 --> 00:43:32,285
It must be a awful big place.

811
00:43:32,395 --> 00:43:35,158
It is, honey.

812
00:43:40,402 --> 00:43:41,801
Shirley...

813
00:43:41,903 --> 00:43:44,303
I've got somethin' to tell you.

814
00:43:44,406 --> 00:43:45,805
A story?

815
00:43:45,907 --> 00:43:47,806
No, not a story.

816
00:43:47,908 --> 00:43:49,842
You know...

817
00:43:51,412 --> 00:43:54,313
ever since your daddy
went to heaven...

818
00:43:54,415 --> 00:43:57,816
your mother's been
awful lonesome for him.

819
00:43:57,918 --> 00:43:59,817
Yes, I know.

820
00:43:59,919 --> 00:44:02,547
Sometimes she cries
and everything.

821
00:44:02,655 --> 00:44:04,384
Well...

822
00:44:04,491 --> 00:44:07,892
today your mother
got so lonesome for your daddy...

823
00:44:07,994 --> 00:44:10,622
that she went to see him.

824
00:44:14,500 --> 00:44:16,866
All the way up to heaven?

825
00:44:16,969 --> 00:44:18,903
Yep.

826
00:44:19,004 --> 00:44:21,370
All the way up to heaven.

827
00:44:23,509 --> 00:44:25,635
They're up there together now.

828
00:44:27,011 --> 00:44:28,911
You mean...

829
00:44:29,013 --> 00:44:32,414
my mother cracked up, too?

830
00:44:32,517 --> 00:44:33,882
Yes.

831
00:44:56,539 --> 00:44:59,440
Would you take these off
for the little girl?

832
00:44:59,542 --> 00:45:01,442
I think I would.

833
00:45:01,544 --> 00:45:03,340
What's to become of her now?

834
00:45:03,445 --> 00:45:05,777
I don't suppose the Smythes
will do anything for her.

835
00:45:05,880 --> 00:45:08,348
Oh, not them.
They're far too selfish.

836
00:45:08,450 --> 00:45:10,543
- Elizabeth-
- Huh?

837
00:45:12,454 --> 00:45:14,354
No, we couldn't do it.

838
00:45:14,456 --> 00:45:16,855
Oh, how I'd love to have her.

839
00:45:16,957 --> 00:45:18,515
She's such a sweet child.

840
00:45:18,625 --> 00:45:19,717
But if we took her...

841
00:45:19,827 --> 00:45:21,385
we'd have to give up
our place here...

842
00:45:21,495 --> 00:45:24,157
and it mightn't be so easy
gettin' another one.

843
00:45:24,264 --> 00:45:25,629
That's what I was thinking.

844
00:45:27,266 --> 00:45:29,359
Well, I've checked up.

845
00:45:29,469 --> 00:45:32,370
As far as I can find out,
there are no relatives.

846
00:45:32,472 --> 00:45:33,871
Now what are we to do?

847
00:45:33,973 --> 00:45:35,338
There's nothing for us to do.

848
00:45:35,441 --> 00:45:36,908
It's no concern of ours.

849
00:45:37,009 --> 00:45:39,909
We have neither a legal
nor a moral responsibility.

850
00:45:40,011 --> 00:45:43,378
I know that, but after all,
the woman worked for us.

851
00:45:43,482 --> 00:45:46,076
People will naturally
expect us to do something.

852
00:45:46,184 --> 00:45:48,049
Maybe one of those aviators...

853
00:45:48,153 --> 00:45:50,383
would like to adopt her.

854
00:45:50,489 --> 00:45:53,013
Well, if they do,
let them go to court.

855
00:45:53,123 --> 00:45:54,556
All that we can do
is to see...

856
00:45:54,658 --> 00:45:56,387
that the little girl
is placed in an institution...

857
00:45:56,494 --> 00:45:57,654
where she'll be cared for.

858
00:45:57,761 --> 00:45:59,922
I'll speak to judge Thompson about it.

859
00:46:00,030 --> 00:46:01,759
Oh, no, you won't!

860
00:46:01,866 --> 00:46:03,493
Oh. Uncle Ned!

861
00:46:03,601 --> 00:46:05,192
Did I hear you say
you were gonna put...

862
00:46:05,301 --> 00:46:06,768
little Bright Eyes
in an orphan asylum?

863
00:46:06,870 --> 00:46:07,996
Who?

864
00:46:08,104 --> 00:46:10,868
Shirley. Bright Eyes, I call her.

865
00:46:10,974 --> 00:46:13,534
I don't care what you call her.

866
00:46:13,643 --> 00:46:15,201
Well, now, Uncle Ned,
you see, uh...

867
00:46:15,311 --> 00:46:16,744
Anita and I have talked
the matter over...

868
00:46:16,846 --> 00:46:18,107
and we've decided...

869
00:46:18,213 --> 00:46:19,737
that since there are
apparently no relatives...

870
00:46:19,848 --> 00:46:21,042
and since of course...

871
00:46:21,149 --> 00:46:22,548
it's impossible for us
to keep Shirley-

872
00:46:22,651 --> 00:46:24,050
Why is it impossible?

873
00:46:24,152 --> 00:46:26,712
Well, really, Uncle Ned,
you could hardly expect us...

874
00:46:26,822 --> 00:46:29,483
to raise our littleJoy
with the child of a servant.

875
00:46:29,590 --> 00:46:31,820
Servant, my eye!

876
00:46:31,926 --> 00:46:34,292
She was just as good as you are.

877
00:46:34,395 --> 00:46:35,987
I don't know where
you get the idea...

878
00:46:36,097 --> 00:46:37,394
you're so high and mighty.

879
00:46:37,498 --> 00:46:39,932
Why, your father
was a retail butcher!

880
00:46:40,034 --> 00:46:42,934
And your father started
life as a bricklayer!

881
00:46:43,036 --> 00:46:44,936
Why, really, Uncle Ned...

882
00:46:45,038 --> 00:46:46,767
you-you mustn't get so excited.

883
00:46:46,873 --> 00:46:49,842
Well, I will if I want to.

884
00:46:49,943 --> 00:46:52,275
Now, listen to me, you two.

885
00:46:52,379 --> 00:46:55,438
I want you to understand
just one thing.

886
00:46:55,548 --> 00:46:57,948
If you ever expect
to get anything out of me...

887
00:46:58,050 --> 00:47:00,644
you're going to be human
enough and decent enough...

888
00:47:00,753 --> 00:47:03,449
to take Shirley
into this house to live.

889
00:47:03,589 --> 00:47:05,989
I'll pay for her board
and her clothes.

890
00:47:06,091 --> 00:47:08,820
Oh, that wouldn't
be necessary, Uncle Ned.

891
00:47:08,927 --> 00:47:11,487
Of course, Uncle Ned.
We had no idea...

892
00:47:11,596 --> 00:47:13,120
you felt this way
about the child.

893
00:47:13,231 --> 00:47:14,289
Well, I do...

894
00:47:14,399 --> 00:47:15,661
and if you
don't want her here...

895
00:47:15,767 --> 00:47:18,167
I guess I can find
some other place for her.

896
00:47:24,775 --> 00:47:25,935
And listen...

897
00:47:26,043 --> 00:47:28,375
I can find another place
for me, too.

898
00:47:38,387 --> 00:47:40,855
Well, this is going
to be perfectly lovely.

899
00:47:40,957 --> 00:47:43,016
Well, you engaged the woman
against my advice.

900
00:47:43,125 --> 00:47:44,352
I told you not to do it.

901
00:47:44,459 --> 00:47:46,290
Are you blaming me
because the woman died...

902
00:47:46,394 --> 00:47:48,191
and left a child
on our hands?

903
00:47:48,296 --> 00:47:49,593
I'm merely pointing out-

904
00:47:49,698 --> 00:47:51,427
Well, don't bother
pointing anything out.

905
00:47:51,533 --> 00:47:53,000
Uncle Ned?

906
00:47:55,804 --> 00:47:57,532
What do you think?

907
00:47:57,638 --> 00:48:00,198
I think you're an old softy.

908
00:48:00,307 --> 00:48:03,140
Well, would you let them put
a child like that in a home?

909
00:48:03,243 --> 00:48:05,507
<i>In my home.</i>

910
00:48:05,613 --> 00:48:07,672
You're not like those two in there.

911
00:48:07,781 --> 00:48:09,680
You're more like me.

912
00:48:09,782 --> 00:48:11,010
Where's Shirley now?

913
00:48:11,117 --> 00:48:12,846
She's down at
the airport with Loop.

914
00:48:12,952 --> 00:48:15,682
Loop? Who's Loop?

915
00:48:15,788 --> 00:48:19,690
Oh. He's that aviator fellow
you were interested in.

916
00:48:19,792 --> 00:48:20,690
Yes.

917
00:48:20,793 --> 00:48:22,350
Uh-huh. Well, uh...

918
00:48:22,461 --> 00:48:25,396
you go down yourself
and bring her back.

919
00:48:27,466 --> 00:48:29,366
I'll go right now.

920
00:48:33,271 --> 00:48:35,261
Whrrr!

921
00:48:42,813 --> 00:48:44,906
How was the trip
to Ensenada?

922
00:48:45,016 --> 00:48:47,176
Terrific. I didn't
have a minute to myself.

923
00:48:47,283 --> 00:48:48,682
I'm gonna sleep from now on.

924
00:48:48,785 --> 00:48:49,911
Hey, Bob.

925
00:48:50,020 --> 00:48:51,647
That's right.

926
00:48:51,755 --> 00:48:53,586
Come on. We're goin'
to San Francisco right away!

927
00:48:53,690 --> 00:48:54,748
Oh, boy!

928
00:49:00,029 --> 00:49:01,553
How'd you like to make a livin'...

929
00:49:01,664 --> 00:49:02,824
flying a guy like that?

930
00:49:02,931 --> 00:49:04,899
Don't squawk.
He could've said Paris!

931
00:49:05,000 --> 00:49:07,093
Ha ha ha!

932
00:49:07,202 --> 00:49:09,898
Whrrr!

933
00:49:10,005 --> 00:49:12,404
Watch, Loop.
I'm gonna bank.

934
00:49:15,843 --> 00:49:18,869
Ha ha ha ha ha!

935
00:49:18,980 --> 00:49:20,811
Ha ha ha ha!

936
00:49:22,450 --> 00:49:25,350
We should've had
our belts on.

937
00:49:25,452 --> 00:49:27,352
You didn't make a bank.

938
00:49:27,454 --> 00:49:29,786
You did a barrel roll!

939
00:49:29,890 --> 00:49:31,790
Now, always remember
one thing-

940
00:49:31,892 --> 00:49:34,861
If you bank too sharply,
you're liable to go into a sideslip.

941
00:49:34,961 --> 00:49:36,450
That's what I did, all right.

942
00:49:36,562 --> 00:49:39,554
I went into a sideslip.

943
00:49:39,665 --> 00:49:41,292
Oh, you!

944
00:49:41,400 --> 00:49:43,300
May I come in?

945
00:49:46,439 --> 00:49:47,428
Hello.

946
00:49:47,540 --> 00:49:48,768
Hello. How are you, dear?

947
00:49:48,873 --> 00:49:51,706
I'm fine, and I'm glad
you came to see me.

948
00:49:51,810 --> 00:49:53,539
Come on and see Loop.

949
00:49:56,915 --> 00:49:58,815
What can I do for you?

950
00:49:58,917 --> 00:50:01,817
I want to talk to you... privately.

951
00:50:01,919 --> 00:50:04,945
Shirley, run over
to the radio room and see...

952
00:50:05,055 --> 00:50:06,784
if the American Airlines
ship is on time.

953
00:50:06,890 --> 00:50:11,224
Why, it was on time
when we asked a while ago.

954
00:50:12,763 --> 00:50:15,424
Well, then, uh...
run over to the hangar...

955
00:50:15,531 --> 00:50:17,362
and find out
if they've gassed my ship.

956
00:50:17,467 --> 00:50:20,925
Well, I know they did
because I watched them.

957
00:50:21,037 --> 00:50:23,505
Come on, take off,
will you, please?

958
00:50:23,606 --> 00:50:24,732
OK.

959
00:50:26,308 --> 00:50:27,832
Whrrr!

960
00:50:29,311 --> 00:50:32,212
Well, you might
ask me to sit down.

961
00:50:32,314 --> 00:50:33,713
I might.

962
00:50:33,815 --> 00:50:35,715
Why are you so bitter?

963
00:50:35,817 --> 00:50:37,717
You ought to know.

964
00:50:37,819 --> 00:50:39,718
Can't you forget the past?

965
00:50:39,820 --> 00:50:42,721
Sure. I can forget a lot of things.

966
00:50:42,823 --> 00:50:46,224
I can forget that
you and I were in love...

967
00:50:46,327 --> 00:50:49,228
and we were engaged
to be married...

968
00:50:49,330 --> 00:50:52,230
and that you
walked out on me.

969
00:50:52,332 --> 00:50:56,132
All that is just
as dead as this.

970
00:50:58,338 --> 00:51:00,238
But I can't forget
that you made a fool of me.

971
00:51:00,340 --> 00:51:02,706
A man usually
remembers that.

972
00:51:02,809 --> 00:51:04,708
Would it make
any difference...

973
00:51:04,810 --> 00:51:06,710
if I said I'm sorry?

974
00:51:06,812 --> 00:51:09,212
Not a bit.
It's a little too late.

975
00:51:09,314 --> 00:51:11,544
You didn't come
all the way over here...

976
00:51:11,650 --> 00:51:13,845
just to tell me that, did you?

977
00:51:13,952 --> 00:51:16,385
No. I came to talk
about Shirley.

978
00:51:16,487 --> 00:51:17,852
What about her?

979
00:51:17,955 --> 00:51:20,219
The Smythes want her to
come and live with them.

980
00:51:20,324 --> 00:51:22,053
Now I'll tell one.

981
00:51:22,160 --> 00:51:24,492
- I mean, Uncle Ned-
- Wait a minute.

982
00:51:24,595 --> 00:51:27,428
You mean you and Uncle Ned
sold the Smythes the idea.

983
00:51:27,532 --> 00:51:29,089
They don't like it
any too well...

984
00:51:29,199 --> 00:51:31,099
but in order to keep in good
with Uncle Ned, they'll do it.

985
00:51:31,201 --> 00:51:32,668
Is that right?

986
00:51:32,769 --> 00:51:34,066
You're being very unfair.

987
00:51:34,171 --> 00:51:36,162
Nothing doing.
You can't have her.

988
00:51:36,273 --> 00:51:38,241
Don't let your feeling
against me...

989
00:51:38,341 --> 00:51:40,400
interfere with the
little girl's future.

990
00:51:40,510 --> 00:51:42,909
I know her father
was your best friend.

991
00:51:43,012 --> 00:51:44,877
I know you love her very dearly.

992
00:51:44,980 --> 00:51:48,211
If you do, you must surely
see that she can't live here...

993
00:51:48,317 --> 00:51:51,218
in a barracks
with a lot of men!

994
00:51:51,320 --> 00:51:53,913
They're pretty good men.

995
00:51:54,022 --> 00:51:56,252
Even so, if there was ever a time...

996
00:51:56,357 --> 00:51:59,622
when a child needed women
around her, it's now!

997
00:51:59,727 --> 00:52:02,218
Oh, I know she can't stay here...

998
00:52:02,330 --> 00:52:04,355
but on the other hand,
I'm not so sure...

999
00:52:04,465 --> 00:52:06,227
the Smythes are the right
people for her to be with.

1000
00:52:06,333 --> 00:52:08,733
But I'm going to take
care of her myself.

1001
00:52:08,836 --> 00:52:11,236
- What about when you go east?
- I'll take her with me.

1002
00:52:11,338 --> 00:52:14,239
Oh, no, you won't. Anyhow,
I'm figuring on getting a house...

1003
00:52:14,341 --> 00:52:16,901
and hiring a woman
to take care of Shirley.

1004
00:52:17,010 --> 00:52:19,273
But that'll take
a little time, won't it?

1005
00:52:19,378 --> 00:52:21,710
Oh, I suppose so.

1006
00:52:24,851 --> 00:52:27,251
I'll tell you what I'll do.

1007
00:52:27,353 --> 00:52:29,753
You can take her for now,
but only with the understanding...

1008
00:52:29,856 --> 00:52:32,551
that when I get a place for her,
Shirley comes with me.

1009
00:52:32,657 --> 00:52:34,056
I love that baby.

1010
00:52:34,159 --> 00:52:36,252
I understand how you feel.

1011
00:52:36,361 --> 00:52:41,094
And, Loop, no matter
what you think of me...

1012
00:52:41,199 --> 00:52:44,292
I think you're the finest
man I've ever known.

1013
00:52:44,401 --> 00:52:47,962
There was a time I thought
you were pretty swell, too.

1014
00:52:49,773 --> 00:52:52,173
Say, Loop,
American Airlines ship is-

1015
00:52:52,276 --> 00:52:55,677
Oh, now I forgot whether
it's four minutes late...

1016
00:52:55,779 --> 00:52:57,678
or four minutes early.

1017
00:52:57,780 --> 00:52:59,873
Never mind.
Come here.

1018
00:53:05,255 --> 00:53:07,655
Honey, would you
like to go back...

1019
00:53:07,757 --> 00:53:10,247
to the Smythes' house
and live there?

1020
00:53:10,359 --> 00:53:11,917
Do I have to?

1021
00:53:12,027 --> 00:53:15,656
For a little while, dear.
We think you should.

1022
00:53:15,764 --> 00:53:18,164
Are you gonna be there?

1023
00:53:18,267 --> 00:53:21,167
Yes, I am, and we'll be
together every day.

1024
00:53:21,269 --> 00:53:23,703
If you're there,
it'll be fine.

1025
00:53:23,804 --> 00:53:27,706
I like you,
and I like Mr. Smith, too.

1026
00:53:27,808 --> 00:53:30,709
All right. Then it's all set.

1027
00:53:32,313 --> 00:53:35,213
Can Loop come
live with us, too?

1028
00:53:35,315 --> 00:53:37,715
Oh, no, dear.
ZJust at the moment...

1029
00:53:37,817 --> 00:53:39,717
I'm afraid that
can't be arranged.

1030
00:53:39,819 --> 00:53:42,219
Oh, no! Not a chance!

1031
00:53:44,291 --> 00:53:46,224
Here, Rags. Here, Rags. Come on.

1032
00:53:46,325 --> 00:53:49,226
I'm gonna let you take
Rags with you, too.

1033
00:53:49,328 --> 00:53:51,728
Oh, goody!
Good old Ragsy.

1034
00:53:51,830 --> 00:53:53,229
Thanks, Loop.

1035
00:53:53,332 --> 00:53:54,731
Oh, that's all right.

1036
00:53:54,833 --> 00:53:57,893
I might as well give
the dog a break, too.

1037
00:53:58,003 --> 00:53:59,299
Don't worry about her.

1038
00:53:59,404 --> 00:54:01,235
Come see her
whenever you like.

1039
00:54:01,339 --> 00:54:02,772
Much obliged.

1040
00:54:05,276 --> 00:54:06,709
So long, sweets.

1041
00:54:08,780 --> 00:54:10,338
If you don't like it there...

1042
00:54:10,448 --> 00:54:12,847
remember what I told you
about the magic ring.

1043
00:54:12,950 --> 00:54:13,974
Send it to me...

1044
00:54:14,084 --> 00:54:15,642
and I'll come and get you.

1045
00:54:19,890 --> 00:54:21,187
Good-bye.

1046
00:54:21,291 --> 00:54:22,690
Good-bye.

1047
00:54:22,793 --> 00:54:24,191
Good-bye, Loop.

1048
00:54:24,293 --> 00:54:25,658
Come on, Ragsy.

1049
00:54:38,306 --> 00:54:40,206
Do you have
much trouble...

1050
00:54:40,308 --> 00:54:42,208
with your little girl?

1051
00:54:42,310 --> 00:54:44,210
Oh, no. She's very good.

1052
00:54:44,312 --> 00:54:46,212
She sleeps all the time.

1053
00:54:46,314 --> 00:54:49,714
Well, I have to spank
mine every day...

1054
00:54:49,817 --> 00:54:52,217
and give her castor oil.

1055
00:54:52,319 --> 00:54:54,219
Now,just listen to her.

1056
00:54:54,321 --> 00:54:56,221
She's crying again!

1057
00:54:56,323 --> 00:54:59,190
Stop crying!
Stop this minute!

1058
00:55:00,927 --> 00:55:03,555
They seem to get along all right.

1059
00:55:03,663 --> 00:55:06,063
Why, of course.
Anyone could get along with Joy...

1060
00:55:06,165 --> 00:55:09,066
but I still think
it's a dreadful imposition.

1061
00:55:09,168 --> 00:55:11,398
I know, but, uh...
it won't last forever.

1062
00:55:11,504 --> 00:55:12,801
What do you mean?

1063
00:55:12,905 --> 00:55:14,735
Well, we can humor
Uncle Ned for a while...

1064
00:55:14,840 --> 00:55:16,330
and then later on,
I can convince him...

1065
00:55:16,441 --> 00:55:18,409
that the child will be
better off somewhere else.

1066
00:55:18,510 --> 00:55:20,808
Shirley is just
one of his whims.

1067
00:55:20,912 --> 00:55:22,504
He'll get tired of her
one of these days.

1068
00:55:22,614 --> 00:55:24,582
I hope so.

1069
00:55:26,717 --> 00:55:27,877
Well, ladies...

1070
00:55:27,985 --> 00:55:30,112
taking your children
out for an airing?

1071
00:55:30,221 --> 00:55:32,121
I'm taking my little girl
to the hospital.

1072
00:55:32,223 --> 00:55:34,623
She's very sick...

1073
00:55:34,725 --> 00:55:38,091
and I'm afraid she'll have
to have an operation.

1074
00:55:38,194 --> 00:55:40,128
Huh. Is that so?

1075
00:55:40,230 --> 00:55:43,631
Yeah. They'll probably
have to cut her leg off.

1076
00:55:43,733 --> 00:55:45,166
Maybe both legs.

1077
00:55:46,736 --> 00:55:49,102
And what's wrong
with your child?

1078
00:55:49,205 --> 00:55:50,728
Nothing. She's fine.

1079
00:55:50,839 --> 00:55:53,239
The only thing
about her is...

1080
00:55:53,342 --> 00:55:56,436
she just won't eat
her spinach.

1081
00:55:56,545 --> 00:56:00,709
Well, we must be going.
Come, Shirley.

1082
00:56:08,756 --> 00:56:10,155
Let's play hospital.

1083
00:56:10,258 --> 00:56:13,785
I'll be the doctor,
and you can be the nurse.

1084
00:56:13,895 --> 00:56:16,158
I'll get a big knife
out of the kitchen...

1085
00:56:16,263 --> 00:56:18,663
and we'll operate
on your doll.

1086
00:56:18,765 --> 00:56:20,790
I don't want Mary Lou
to be operated on.

1087
00:56:20,901 --> 00:56:23,301
I don't care.
You have to do as I say...

1088
00:56:23,403 --> 00:56:25,234
and play the way I want to.

1089
00:56:25,338 --> 00:56:27,238
- I don't, either.
- Yes, you do.

1090
00:56:27,340 --> 00:56:28,966
This is my house
and my yard...

1091
00:56:29,075 --> 00:56:31,600
and you're nothing
but an old charity.

1092
00:56:31,710 --> 00:56:37,046
- I am not!
- Yes, you are, 'cause I heard my papa tell my mama.

1093
00:56:42,187 --> 00:56:44,621
Let's do something else.

1094
00:56:44,722 --> 00:56:47,691
Do you want to play a game?

1095
00:56:47,792 --> 00:56:49,259
What kind of a game?

1096
00:56:49,360 --> 00:56:50,258
Train wreck.

1097
00:56:50,361 --> 00:56:51,453
How do you play it?

1098
00:56:51,563 --> 00:56:52,790
I'll show you.

1099
00:56:52,896 --> 00:56:55,729
You stand right here
and don't move.

1100
00:56:57,734 --> 00:57:00,703
All right, now, don't move.
Here comes the train!

1101
00:57:00,804 --> 00:57:02,169
Woo woo!

1102
00:57:03,440 --> 00:57:05,373
Aah aah!

1103
00:57:13,749 --> 00:57:16,650
Mama! Mama!

1104
00:57:16,752 --> 00:57:18,719
Shirley pushed me!

1105
00:57:20,255 --> 00:57:22,655
What's the matter
with that imp?

1106
00:57:22,757 --> 00:57:24,657
She's a very difficult child.

1107
00:57:24,759 --> 00:57:25,783
Difficult? Huh!

1108
00:57:25,894 --> 00:57:28,658
I can think of a better word.

1109
00:57:28,763 --> 00:57:31,731
Uncle Ned, I think you
should speak to Anita...

1110
00:57:31,832 --> 00:57:33,459
about the way
ZJoy treats Shirley.

1111
00:57:33,567 --> 00:57:35,831
No use talkin' to her.

1112
00:57:35,936 --> 00:57:38,734
I got somethin'
better up my sleeve.

1113
00:57:38,839 --> 00:57:39,806
What?

1114
00:57:39,907 --> 00:57:40,771
You'll see.

1115
00:57:41,976 --> 00:57:43,704
Well, it's your move.

1116
00:57:45,278 --> 00:57:48,213
Uh... you only got one move.

1117
00:57:55,287 --> 00:57:56,686
Ha ha ha!

1118
00:57:56,788 --> 00:57:58,187
There you are!

1119
00:57:58,290 --> 00:57:59,689
Look at that!

1120
00:57:59,791 --> 00:58:01,156
You give up?

1121
00:58:04,263 --> 00:58:05,594
What was it you wanted?

1122
00:58:05,697 --> 00:58:07,028
I don't know whether
you know it or not...

1123
00:58:07,132 --> 00:58:08,359
but I'm Shirley's godfather.

1124
00:58:08,466 --> 00:58:09,899
- Oh, is that so?
- Really?

1125
00:58:10,001 --> 00:58:11,559
So naturally I want to do
the best I can for her.

1126
00:58:11,669 --> 00:58:13,136
Yes, of course.

1127
00:58:13,237 --> 00:58:15,398
When you wanted her to stay
here and live with you...

1128
00:58:15,506 --> 00:58:17,235
I thought it would be
a good idea.

1129
00:58:17,341 --> 00:58:18,706
I knew you'd be nice to her.

1130
00:58:18,809 --> 00:58:22,539
It isn't hard to be nice
to such a sweet child.

1131
00:58:22,646 --> 00:58:24,409
I'm glad you feel that way...

1132
00:58:24,514 --> 00:58:26,106
because Shirley means
more to me than anybody else...

1133
00:58:26,216 --> 00:58:27,478
in the world.

1134
00:58:27,584 --> 00:58:30,678
That's why I thought
I'd come and ask you-

1135
00:58:30,787 --> 00:58:32,186
Yes?

1136
00:58:32,289 --> 00:58:34,552
I want to take her
to live with me.

1137
00:58:34,657 --> 00:58:36,056
And I hope you'll
let me have her.

1138
00:58:36,158 --> 00:58:38,023
What's that?

1139
00:58:38,127 --> 00:58:39,719
Hey, what's all this?

1140
00:58:39,828 --> 00:58:40,726
Why-

1141
00:58:40,829 --> 00:58:42,592
Let me explain, dear.

1142
00:58:42,698 --> 00:58:44,393
You're that aviator
fellow, ain't ya?

1143
00:58:44,500 --> 00:58:45,693
That's right.

1144
00:58:45,800 --> 00:58:47,233
I don't like airplanes.

1145
00:58:47,335 --> 00:58:48,996
Well, I don't like wheelchairs.

1146
00:58:49,103 --> 00:58:50,934
Well, you stay
in the airplane business...

1147
00:58:51,039 --> 00:58:53,269
and you'll wind up in one.

1148
00:58:54,475 --> 00:58:56,807
What's he doin' here?

1149
00:58:56,911 --> 00:58:58,400
Well... you see, Uncle Ned...

1150
00:58:58,512 --> 00:59:00,605
Mr. Merritt thinks
it's a good idea...

1151
00:59:00,714 --> 00:59:02,272
for Shirley to live with him.

1152
00:59:02,382 --> 00:59:05,579
What?! He wants to take
Shirley away from here?

1153
00:59:05,686 --> 00:59:07,415
Are you married?

1154
00:59:07,521 --> 00:59:09,079
No, I'm not.

1155
00:59:09,189 --> 00:59:11,088
How much do you make?

1156
00:59:11,190 --> 00:59:12,589
Enough to support myself.

1157
00:59:12,692 --> 00:59:13,590
Where do you live?

1158
00:59:13,693 --> 00:59:14,591
At the airport.

1159
00:59:14,694 --> 00:59:15,752
Where do you eat?

1160
00:59:15,861 --> 00:59:17,021
In restaurants.

1161
00:59:17,129 --> 00:59:20,098
You've got a lot
of nerve, young fella.

1162
00:59:20,199 --> 00:59:22,099
How can you take care
of a child...

1163
00:59:22,201 --> 00:59:25,931
when you haven't got a home
or a wife or even a cook?

1164
00:59:26,037 --> 00:59:29,598
Well, maybe I've got
something else she needs.

1165
00:59:29,708 --> 00:59:32,108
- What?
- Love, that's what.

1166
00:59:32,210 --> 00:59:33,609
Aw, fiddlesticks!

1167
00:59:33,712 --> 00:59:36,612
We all love her
here, don't we?!

1168
00:59:36,714 --> 00:59:38,113
Yes, Uncle Ned.

1169
00:59:38,215 --> 00:59:39,614
Well, you can't have her!

1170
00:59:39,717 --> 00:59:41,184
- Who says so?
- I say so.

1171
00:59:41,285 --> 00:59:43,082
I've got more right
to her than you have.

1172
00:59:43,187 --> 00:59:44,848
Aw, nonsense. You haven't
any right at all.

1173
00:59:44,955 --> 00:59:47,150
Well, we'll see about that!

1174
00:59:47,257 --> 00:59:49,122
Hey, young fella!

1175
00:59:49,225 --> 00:59:51,785
If you want to see about it...

1176
00:59:51,894 --> 00:59:53,623
you see my lawyers!

1177
00:59:53,730 --> 00:59:55,061
Lawyers?

1178
00:59:55,164 --> 00:59:56,825
Lawyers?

1179
00:59:56,933 --> 00:59:59,163
That's what I said. Lawyers.

1180
00:59:59,269 --> 01:00:02,760
I'm taking legal steps
to adopt Shirley.

1181
01:00:04,506 --> 01:00:05,905
Good heavens!

1182
01:00:07,976 --> 01:00:09,671
So that's where he went yesterday.

1183
01:00:09,778 --> 01:00:11,075
You can't get away with this!

1184
01:00:11,179 --> 01:00:12,202
Oh, I can't, eh?

1185
01:00:12,313 --> 01:00:13,905
No! I'm gonna give you a fight!

1186
01:00:14,015 --> 01:00:16,506
I'll get lawyers myself!
We'll let the court decide!

1187
01:00:16,617 --> 01:00:18,141
Is that so?

1188
01:00:19,854 --> 01:00:21,754
You haven't got money
enough to fight me!

1189
01:00:21,856 --> 01:00:24,653
I'll get it. I don't care
if you've got $90 million!

1190
01:00:24,758 --> 01:00:26,817
You're not gonna take
Shirley away from me!

1191
01:00:26,926 --> 01:00:29,656
Ha! I've got the best
lawyers in the country!

1192
01:00:29,763 --> 01:00:31,731
Ha ha ha!

1193
01:00:31,831 --> 01:00:33,128
Loop!

1194
01:00:35,335 --> 01:00:38,201
You put one over
on me again, didn't you?

1195
01:00:38,304 --> 01:00:40,898
No. I didn't.
I didn't know about it.

1196
01:00:41,006 --> 01:00:42,837
You expect me
to believe that?

1197
01:00:42,941 --> 01:00:44,101
Yes.

1198
01:00:44,209 --> 01:00:45,335
OK.

1199
01:00:45,444 --> 01:00:48,845
Loop, from now on,
I'm on your side.

1200
01:00:48,947 --> 01:00:50,106
Why?

1201
01:00:50,214 --> 01:00:53,115
Because if Shirley
means so much to you...

1202
01:00:53,217 --> 01:00:55,117
then you're the one
who should have her.

1203
01:00:55,219 --> 01:00:58,120
For a child, love counts
more than anything.

1204
01:00:58,222 --> 01:01:00,747
ZJust for a child, huh?

1205
01:01:00,892 --> 01:01:02,358
For anyone.

1206
01:01:02,459 --> 01:01:05,360
I'm glad you found that out.

1207
01:01:21,410 --> 01:01:23,310
There, now.

1208
01:01:24,914 --> 01:01:27,313
Pleasant dreams, dear,
and go right to sleep.

1209
01:01:27,415 --> 01:01:29,315
I don't want to go to sleep...

1210
01:01:29,417 --> 01:01:31,146
but I'll try.

1211
01:01:31,252 --> 01:01:33,015
That's a good little girl.

1212
01:01:35,323 --> 01:01:37,223
Good night, Shirley.

1213
01:01:37,325 --> 01:01:39,225
Good night, Mrs. Smythe.

1214
01:01:39,327 --> 01:01:40,554
And remember, Shirley...

1215
01:01:40,661 --> 01:01:42,629
I don't want to have to
speak to you again...

1216
01:01:42,730 --> 01:01:45,858
about having that awful
little dog in your bed.

1217
01:01:48,902 --> 01:01:50,301
It isn't healthful.

1218
01:01:50,404 --> 01:01:52,803
And besides,
I think the dog has fleas.

1219
01:01:52,905 --> 01:01:55,305
Oh, no. He hasn't got fleas.

1220
01:01:55,408 --> 01:01:58,241
He just scratches that way
because he's itchy.

1221
01:01:58,344 --> 01:02:01,905
Well, I don't want him
here in this bedroom.

1222
01:02:02,014 --> 01:02:03,413
Is that understood?

1223
01:02:03,516 --> 01:02:04,846
Yes, ma'am.

1224
01:02:07,953 --> 01:02:09,853
Good night,Joy, darling.

1225
01:02:15,460 --> 01:02:16,688
Hey!

1226
01:02:16,795 --> 01:02:18,022
What?

1227
01:02:18,129 --> 01:02:20,427
Do you want to play burglars?

1228
01:02:20,531 --> 01:02:23,932
No. I want to go to sleep.

1229
01:02:27,905 --> 01:02:30,099
Come on, Rags.

1230
01:02:30,206 --> 01:02:34,802
Ooh! You've got that
awful dog in your bed...

1231
01:02:34,911 --> 01:02:37,311
after mommy
told you not to!

1232
01:02:37,414 --> 01:02:38,813
I'm gonna tell.

1233
01:02:38,915 --> 01:02:40,314
Mama!

1234
01:02:40,417 --> 01:02:42,816
You don't have to
yell for your mother...

1235
01:02:42,918 --> 01:02:45,113
and you don't have to
tell her, either...

1236
01:02:45,220 --> 01:02:46,983
you old tattletale.

1237
01:02:47,089 --> 01:02:49,819
I'll take Rags downstairs.

1238
01:02:49,925 --> 01:02:52,519
Come on, Rags, good old dog.

1239
01:02:56,397 --> 01:02:58,297
I thought about it
and thought about it...

1240
01:02:58,399 --> 01:03:00,526
and I'll be hanged-

1241
01:03:00,635 --> 01:03:02,830
Pardon me, dear-
if I know what to do.

1242
01:03:02,937 --> 01:03:05,838
The minute I heard him say
he'd seen his lawyers...

1243
01:03:05,940 --> 01:03:08,169
I felt a cold chill
go down my back.

1244
01:03:08,275 --> 01:03:09,867
He may have
changed his will.

1245
01:03:09,976 --> 01:03:11,409
He may have left us
out of it entirely.

1246
01:03:11,511 --> 01:03:12,978
Oh, it's intolerable.

1247
01:03:13,079 --> 01:03:14,478
Yes, you're right, dear...

1248
01:03:14,581 --> 01:03:16,378
and all because
he took a fancy...

1249
01:03:16,483 --> 01:03:17,848
to a 5-year-old orphan.

1250
01:03:17,951 --> 01:03:19,247
There's been nothing
but trouble...

1251
01:03:19,351 --> 01:03:20,648
ever since that child
came into this house.

1252
01:03:20,753 --> 01:03:21,913
I wish we'd never seen her.

1253
01:03:22,021 --> 01:03:23,750
If you'd only taken my-

1254
01:03:23,856 --> 01:03:26,017
Now, don't tell me again
that it's all my fault...

1255
01:03:26,125 --> 01:03:27,990
for hiring the woman.

1256
01:03:28,093 --> 01:03:29,993
All right, dear.

1257
01:03:30,095 --> 01:03:31,925
Well, what are we
going to do about it?

1258
01:03:32,030 --> 01:03:34,828
If we could find some way of
getting rid of the child.

1259
01:03:34,933 --> 01:03:36,901
Heaven knows
she's not wanted here.

1260
01:03:37,001 --> 01:03:39,731
Why don't you bribe
that aviator fellow...

1261
01:03:39,838 --> 01:03:42,329
to take her out of the state?

1262
01:03:42,440 --> 01:03:44,339
Now, that's an idea.

1263
01:03:44,441 --> 01:03:45,999
But what would
Uncle Ned think?

1264
01:03:46,109 --> 01:03:47,701
Oh, I don't know.

1265
01:03:47,811 --> 01:03:51,212
I'm so sick of hearing that
child's name, I could scream.

1266
01:03:51,315 --> 01:03:53,476
She's practically
disrupted the family.

1267
01:03:53,584 --> 01:03:57,576
I know, dear. But we've got
to find some way out of it.

1268
01:04:33,888 --> 01:04:36,412
Say, what's
a three-letter word...

1269
01:04:36,523 --> 01:04:38,013
for Peer Gynt's mother?

1270
01:04:41,394 --> 01:04:43,794
What's the matter,
Loop? You low?

1271
01:04:43,897 --> 01:04:46,297
How could I
make some money?

1272
01:04:46,399 --> 01:04:47,797
What for?

1273
01:04:47,900 --> 01:04:49,094
Well, I gotta hire some lawyers.

1274
01:04:49,201 --> 01:04:50,566
Why don't you marry the girl?

1275
01:04:50,669 --> 01:04:53,297
Cut out the wisecracks,
will you? I'm serious.

1276
01:04:53,405 --> 01:04:55,305
I don't know, Loop.
Flyers never have any money.

1277
01:04:55,407 --> 01:04:56,806
You know that.

1278
01:04:56,909 --> 01:04:58,899
Yeah, I know it.

1279
01:05:01,412 --> 01:05:03,312
Wow! What a night!

1280
01:05:04,415 --> 01:05:05,814
Heavy weather, huh?

1281
01:05:05,917 --> 01:05:07,316
Terrific.

1282
01:05:07,418 --> 01:05:09,318
I hear everything's on the ground.
Nothing moving.

1283
01:05:09,420 --> 01:05:12,320
That's right.
Zero zero all along the line.

1284
01:05:12,422 --> 01:05:13,821
Boy, oh, boy.

1285
01:05:18,695 --> 01:05:20,890
Hello, everybody.

1286
01:05:23,033 --> 01:05:24,465
Shirley!

1287
01:05:25,534 --> 01:05:26,933
What's happened?

1288
01:05:27,036 --> 01:05:28,628
Shirley,
what are you doing out...

1289
01:05:28,737 --> 01:05:31,467
on a night like this?
Why, you're soakin' wet.

1290
01:05:31,574 --> 01:05:34,270
Come on, now. You gotta get
those clothes off and dried out.

1291
01:05:34,376 --> 01:05:35,274
Hello.

1292
01:05:35,377 --> 01:05:36,274
Hello, honey.

1293
01:05:36,377 --> 01:05:37,401
Hello, Shirley.

1294
01:05:40,882 --> 01:05:42,144
Are you all dressed?

1295
01:05:42,250 --> 01:05:43,274
Yes.

1296
01:05:43,384 --> 01:05:44,874
Did you dry yourself off good?

1297
01:05:44,986 --> 01:05:46,851
- I did.
- OK.

1298
01:05:52,392 --> 01:05:53,791
Ha ha ha!

1299
01:05:53,894 --> 01:05:55,794
You sure look swell.

1300
01:05:55,896 --> 01:05:57,830
They fit you fine.

1301
01:05:58,899 --> 01:06:00,423
Now, then...

1302
01:06:00,534 --> 01:06:02,296
what's the big idea?

1303
01:06:02,401 --> 01:06:05,837
I don't want to live with
the Smythes anymore, Loop.

1304
01:06:05,938 --> 01:06:07,803
I want to stay with you.

1305
01:06:07,907 --> 01:06:10,808
I want you to stay
with me, Shirley.

1306
01:06:10,910 --> 01:06:12,810
And I'm gonna try
and fix it so you can.

1307
01:06:12,912 --> 01:06:15,311
Oh, goody!

1308
01:06:15,413 --> 01:06:17,313
Now, then...
off you go to sleep...

1309
01:06:17,415 --> 01:06:19,280
and we'll talk
everything over tomorrow.

1310
01:06:19,384 --> 01:06:21,318
You're not mad at me
for coming here...

1311
01:06:21,419 --> 01:06:23,011
are you, Loop?

1312
01:06:23,121 --> 01:06:26,283
Yes, I am very, very mad.

1313
01:06:26,390 --> 01:06:27,618
Ha ha ha!

1314
01:06:27,725 --> 01:06:29,022
Come on.

1315
01:06:29,126 --> 01:06:30,559
Ha ha ha!

1316
01:06:41,904 --> 01:06:43,303
? Ohhh?

1317
01:06:43,406 --> 01:06:45,806
? He flies
through the air?

1318
01:06:45,908 --> 01:06:47,500
? With the greatest
of ease?

1319
01:06:47,610 --> 01:06:49,669
? This daring young man?

1320
01:06:49,779 --> 01:06:52,178
? On his flying trapeze?

1321
01:06:52,280 --> 01:06:54,180
? Well, his movements
were graceful?

1322
01:06:54,282 --> 01:06:56,182
? The girls he would please?

1323
01:06:56,284 --> 01:06:57,512
? This daring young man?

1324
01:06:57,619 --> 01:07:00,315
? On his flying trapeze?

1325
01:07:00,422 --> 01:07:01,821
Well, good morning, Anita.

1326
01:07:01,923 --> 01:07:03,185
Good morning, Uncle Ned.

1327
01:07:03,291 --> 01:07:04,314
Good morning,John.

1328
01:07:04,425 --> 01:07:05,414
Good morning, Uncle Ned.

1329
01:07:05,526 --> 01:07:07,323
Beautiful morning, isn't it?

1330
01:07:09,430 --> 01:07:12,331
Do you feel all right, Uncle Ned?

1331
01:07:12,433 --> 01:07:15,334
My boy, I never felt
better in my life.

1332
01:07:19,339 --> 01:07:20,738
Tony!

1333
01:07:20,840 --> 01:07:23,240
I sent him out for
some breakfast, Loop.

1334
01:07:23,343 --> 01:07:24,742
What's the matter?
Aren't you workin'?

1335
01:07:24,844 --> 01:07:26,744
Not today. I'm no hero.

1336
01:07:26,846 --> 01:07:29,245
Aw, it's not that tough, is it?

1337
01:07:29,348 --> 01:07:31,873
<i>Ladies and gentlemen,
here's news of national import.</i>

1338
01:07:31,984 --> 01:07:33,542
<i>Two mail planes
are reported missing...</i>

1339
01:07:33,652 --> 01:07:35,950
<i>in the worst storm the West
has known in years.</i>

1340
01:07:36,055 --> 01:07:38,615
<i>A blizzard is raging
over the Rockies...</i>

1341
01:07:38,724 --> 01:07:40,783
<i>which has completely disrupted
rail and air traffic.</i>

1342
01:07:40,893 --> 01:07:42,883
<i>All transcontinental
passenger planes...</i>

1343
01:07:42,994 --> 01:07:45,428
<i>have been ordered grounded
until the weather breaks.</i>

1344
01:07:45,530 --> 01:07:47,794
<i>That's 30 for this morning.
This is Sam Hayes speaking.</i>

1345
01:07:47,899 --> 01:07:49,696
<i>I'll see you tonight
at 10.00. Good day, all.</i>

1346
01:07:49,801 --> 01:07:51,769
I'm ready for breakfast now, Loop.

1347
01:07:51,869 --> 01:07:54,428
I was gonna have
some chow brought down...

1348
01:07:54,538 --> 01:07:56,563
but I guess we'll
have to go and get it.

1349
01:07:56,673 --> 01:07:59,073
And then, young lady,
you're going to have to go home.

1350
01:07:59,176 --> 01:08:01,770
Oh, Loop.
Why can't I stay here?

1351
01:08:01,878 --> 01:08:04,813
Can't you be a soldier and
stick it out for a little while?

1352
01:08:04,915 --> 01:08:06,905
I don't want to.

1353
01:08:07,016 --> 01:08:08,916
You don't want to live
in a swell house...

1354
01:08:09,018 --> 01:08:12,249
go to a nice school,
and be educated and refined?

1355
01:08:12,354 --> 01:08:14,117
I don't want to be refined.

1356
01:08:14,223 --> 01:08:15,986
I want to be like you.

1357
01:08:17,893 --> 01:08:20,759
All right.
Let's eat and talk it over.

1358
01:08:20,862 --> 01:08:22,227
Now, come on. Bundle up warm.

1359
01:08:24,866 --> 01:08:27,767
Well, children,
I want you to know...

1360
01:08:27,869 --> 01:08:30,030
that I'm about
to change my will.

1361
01:08:32,740 --> 01:08:34,264
I'm adopting Shirley...

1362
01:08:34,374 --> 01:08:36,672
and I'm setting aside
a trust fund for her.

1363
01:08:36,777 --> 01:08:37,937
What?

1364
01:08:38,045 --> 01:08:40,275
You two have
nothing to worry about...

1365
01:08:40,380 --> 01:08:42,905
so long as you
behave yourselves.

1366
01:08:44,383 --> 01:08:45,509
Mama!

1367
01:08:45,618 --> 01:08:46,642
Mama!

1368
01:08:46,753 --> 01:08:47,742
Mama!

1369
01:08:47,854 --> 01:08:49,287
Mama! Mama!

1370
01:08:49,388 --> 01:08:51,413
- Shirley's gone!
- What?

1371
01:08:51,524 --> 01:08:53,822
Yeah! She didn't sleep
in her bed all night...

1372
01:08:53,926 --> 01:08:57,190
'cause I woke up and looked.
She must've run away!

1373
01:08:57,295 --> 01:08:59,786
She wouldn't have run away
without some reason!

1374
01:08:59,898 --> 01:09:01,490
Did you have anything
to do with this?

1375
01:09:01,600 --> 01:09:03,261
Why, of course not, Uncle Ned.

1376
01:09:03,368 --> 01:09:05,461
She's gone to that aviator fella!

1377
01:09:05,570 --> 01:09:08,470
Get police! Get detectives!
Get the army!

1378
01:09:08,572 --> 01:09:10,472
But go to that airport
and bring her home!

1379
01:09:10,574 --> 01:09:11,871
Yes, Uncle Ned.

1380
01:09:11,976 --> 01:09:13,841
There'd better be some
action around here now...

1381
01:09:13,944 --> 01:09:15,172
I'll tell you that!

1382
01:09:25,288 --> 01:09:26,721
You see, honey?

1383
01:09:26,823 --> 01:09:29,223
Man's just learning what
the birds knew all the time.

1384
01:09:29,325 --> 01:09:30,690
What?

1385
01:09:30,794 --> 01:09:34,194
You never saw birds fly
in bad weather, did you?

1386
01:09:34,296 --> 01:09:36,230
They have
too much sense for that.

1387
01:09:38,801 --> 01:09:42,498
Listen. Am I working for you,
or you working for me?

1388
01:09:42,604 --> 01:09:43,662
I'm workin' for you.

1389
01:09:43,772 --> 01:09:44,966
Well, then you listen to me.

1390
01:09:45,073 --> 01:09:46,562
This has gotta be
in New York tomorrow.

1391
01:09:46,674 --> 01:09:48,665
It means a lot of money to me.
You're gonna fly it there.

1392
01:09:48,776 --> 01:09:49,834
Not me.

1393
01:09:49,944 --> 01:09:51,343
What do you mean, not you?

1394
01:09:51,445 --> 01:09:53,037
I mean the weather's too bad.

1395
01:09:53,147 --> 01:09:54,637
There won't be one ship
take off from here today.

1396
01:09:54,749 --> 01:09:56,376
- It's too dangerous.
- You don't understand.

1397
01:09:56,484 --> 01:09:58,417
This has got to be
in New York tomorrow.

1398
01:09:58,518 --> 01:09:59,849
That's all I know.

1399
01:09:59,953 --> 01:10:01,784
Well, I'm sorry, it can't be done.

1400
01:10:01,888 --> 01:10:03,583
I've got a wife and two children...

1401
01:10:03,690 --> 01:10:05,385
and they mean more
to me than this job.

1402
01:10:05,492 --> 01:10:07,016
You mean I gotta
get someone else?

1403
01:10:07,127 --> 01:10:09,220
You sure do.

1404
01:10:09,329 --> 01:10:11,296
All right. You're through.

1405
01:10:11,397 --> 01:10:13,797
I'd give $1,000 for this flight.

1406
01:10:13,899 --> 01:10:16,265
There must be someone around
that wants that kind of money.

1407
01:10:16,368 --> 01:10:17,596
You won't get anyone
to fly today.

1408
01:10:17,703 --> 01:10:20,763
Well, that's my worry.
I'll find somebody.

1409
01:10:21,974 --> 01:10:23,440
Oh, my! Come on!

1410
01:10:23,541 --> 01:10:24,940
Come on, Rags.

1411
01:10:30,548 --> 01:10:31,947
Who's Loop Merritt?

1412
01:10:32,050 --> 01:10:33,449
I am.

1413
01:10:34,586 --> 01:10:37,816
You fly to New York for me?

1414
01:10:37,921 --> 01:10:39,479
Not today.

1415
01:10:39,590 --> 01:10:43,924
They told me you were a
flyer with plenty of nerve.

1416
01:10:44,027 --> 01:10:46,222
Nerve is one thing,
and being crazy is another.

1417
01:10:46,330 --> 01:10:48,320
Anybody who takes a ship
up today is crazy.

1418
01:10:48,431 --> 01:10:51,366
There's $1,000 in it for you.

1419
01:10:53,436 --> 01:10:55,836
I could use 1,000, all right.

1420
01:10:55,938 --> 01:10:57,838
Mister, you got a bet.

1421
01:10:57,940 --> 01:11:00,170
This has to be delivered in
New York tomorrow morning.

1422
01:11:00,276 --> 01:11:01,936
Leave the check in the office
with Major Moseley.

1423
01:11:02,043 --> 01:11:03,408
I'll do that right now...

1424
01:11:03,511 --> 01:11:05,342
and I'll meet you
in my hangar in 10 minutes.

1425
01:11:07,449 --> 01:11:09,815
You're not really gonna
fly today, are you, Loop?

1426
01:11:09,918 --> 01:11:11,249
I sure am.

1427
01:11:11,353 --> 01:11:13,183
Don't be crazy.
You'll kill yourself!.

1428
01:11:13,287 --> 01:11:14,584
Didn't you ever
need money so badly...

1429
01:11:14,688 --> 01:11:15,950
you were willing
to risk your life for it?

1430
01:11:16,056 --> 01:11:17,614
Sure, but on a day like-

1431
01:11:17,725 --> 01:11:19,488
I know, but I need $1,000,
and I need it for a good reason.

1432
01:11:19,593 --> 01:11:20,821
No one should fly
in this weather.

1433
01:11:20,928 --> 01:11:22,759
I fly better
in weather like this.

1434
01:11:30,536 --> 01:11:31,901
Eddie, come here.

1435
01:11:35,408 --> 01:11:37,342
Take Shirley home, will you?

1436
01:11:37,443 --> 01:11:39,535
Sure, Loop.

1437
01:11:39,645 --> 01:11:41,044
So long, baby.

1438
01:11:41,146 --> 01:11:42,545
Be a nice fella
and wait till I get back.

1439
01:11:42,648 --> 01:11:44,343
I'll wait right here for you.

1440
01:11:44,449 --> 01:11:45,973
Oh, no. You have to go home.

1441
01:11:46,084 --> 01:11:49,281
No. I'm never going back there.

1442
01:11:49,388 --> 01:11:52,652
Aw, Shirley. I'm making
this flight to get money...

1443
01:11:52,757 --> 01:11:55,225
so that I can take you
and keep you with me always.

1444
01:11:55,326 --> 01:11:57,453
But for now, you'll have to
go back to the Smythes'.

1445
01:11:57,561 --> 01:12:00,359
Won't you do that for me?

1446
01:12:00,464 --> 01:12:02,364
All right, Loop...

1447
01:12:02,466 --> 01:12:04,194
but hurry back.

1448
01:12:17,479 --> 01:12:19,310
You wait in here
out of the wind, honey.

1449
01:12:19,415 --> 01:12:20,746
I'll be right back.

1450
01:12:41,702 --> 01:12:44,102
So long, Loop. Lots of luck.

1451
01:12:44,204 --> 01:12:46,035
Why don't you call it off, Loop?

1452
01:12:46,139 --> 01:12:47,231
Nothin' doin'.

1453
01:12:47,341 --> 01:12:49,502
Hey,just a minute!
Where's Shirley?

1454
01:12:49,609 --> 01:12:51,509
Don't tell me you're worried.

1455
01:12:51,611 --> 01:12:54,044
Never mind the funny stuff.
If you've got that kid...

1456
01:12:54,146 --> 01:12:55,613
you're in a tough spot.

1457
01:12:55,715 --> 01:12:58,343
Well, wise guy, I haven't got her.
I sent her home.

1458
01:12:58,451 --> 01:12:59,941
She'll be at your house
before you get there.

1459
01:13:00,052 --> 01:13:01,019
You sent her home?

1460
01:13:01,120 --> 01:13:02,519
Yes, I sent her home!

1461
01:13:02,621 --> 01:13:04,418
You know I could have you
arrested for kidnapping.

1462
01:13:04,523 --> 01:13:05,853
We'll take that up
at the next meeting.

1463
01:13:05,957 --> 01:13:06,946
So long, fellas.

1464
01:13:49,398 --> 01:13:51,798
- Well, where is she?
- Isn't she here?

1465
01:13:51,900 --> 01:13:53,800
- She is not.
- She ought to be.

1466
01:13:53,902 --> 01:13:55,300
Sure, she should be,
but she isn't.

1467
01:13:55,403 --> 01:13:56,461
Are you a detective?

1468
01:13:56,570 --> 01:13:57,628
Yes, sir.

1469
01:13:57,738 --> 01:13:58,762
Well, I'm not, but if I was one...

1470
01:13:58,873 --> 01:13:59,965
I'd figure out where she is.

1471
01:14:00,074 --> 01:14:00,972
Now, Mr. Smythe-

1472
01:14:01,075 --> 01:14:01,973
Smith's my name!

1473
01:14:02,076 --> 01:14:03,100
You know what I think?

1474
01:14:03,210 --> 01:14:04,677
I didn't know you could think!

1475
01:14:04,779 --> 01:14:06,406
I think that aviator
took her with him.

1476
01:14:06,514 --> 01:14:07,571
He was going on a flight
when we got there.

1477
01:14:07,680 --> 01:14:08,669
Say, that's right!

1478
01:14:08,782 --> 01:14:10,272
You say he was goin' away?

1479
01:14:10,383 --> 01:14:11,611
- Yes.
- Sure, he's got her!

1480
01:14:11,718 --> 01:14:13,686
He's taken her with him!

1481
01:14:13,787 --> 01:14:15,152
Call the police!
Call my lawyers!

1482
01:14:15,255 --> 01:14:16,984
Now, take it easy, Uncle Ned.

1483
01:14:17,090 --> 01:14:18,114
Ah, get out.

1484
01:14:18,224 --> 01:14:20,282
Hurry, man! Hurry!

1485
01:14:20,392 --> 01:14:21,859
Have them in a moment,
Mr. Smith.

1486
01:14:21,960 --> 01:14:23,757
Hello. This is Hall speaking.

1487
01:14:23,862 --> 01:14:24,794
I want to report a kidnapping.

1488
01:14:24,897 --> 01:14:26,797
I'll spend $10,000-

1489
01:14:26,899 --> 01:14:30,596
Anything to get her
back safe and sound.

1490
01:14:34,906 --> 01:14:37,807
<i>Burbank, Burbank. Zero zero.</i>

1491
01:14:37,909 --> 01:14:42,312
<i>Dense fog. Zero.
Temperature 50.</i>

1492
01:14:42,413 --> 01:14:44,937
<i>Dew point 50.</i>

1493
01:14:45,048 --> 01:14:46,640
<i>Barometer 29.80.</i>

1494
01:14:46,750 --> 01:14:48,115
<i>Winds west 3.</i>

1495
01:14:50,921 --> 01:14:53,822
<i>All airports have been asked
to notify police...</i>

1496
01:14:53,924 --> 01:14:57,359
<i>if plane NC13843 lands.</i>

1497
01:14:57,460 --> 01:14:59,485
<i>The pilot,James Merritt...</i>

1498
01:14:59,595 --> 01:15:01,790
<i>is suspected ofkidnapping
Shirley Blake...</i>

1499
01:15:01,897 --> 01:15:03,330
<i>5 years old.</i>

1500
01:15:03,432 --> 01:15:05,332
Ha! Ha ha!

1501
01:15:05,434 --> 01:15:07,459
Ha ha ha ha!

1502
01:15:18,847 --> 01:15:21,281
Shirley! Come here.

1503
01:15:26,353 --> 01:15:28,753
How did you get in here?

1504
01:15:28,856 --> 01:15:31,791
I got in where the baggage goes.

1505
01:15:33,360 --> 01:15:35,259
Don't be mad, Loop.

1506
01:15:35,361 --> 01:15:36,919
This is the first time in my life...

1507
01:15:37,029 --> 01:15:38,621
I ever felt like spanking you.

1508
01:15:38,731 --> 01:15:41,165
Didn't you tell me
to send you this ring...

1509
01:15:41,267 --> 01:15:42,700
if I wanted you
to come get me?

1510
01:15:42,802 --> 01:15:43,894
That's right.

1511
01:15:44,003 --> 01:15:45,493
Well, I was going to send it...

1512
01:15:45,605 --> 01:15:48,835
but I couldn't get it off,
so I brought it myself. See?

1513
01:15:48,940 --> 01:15:52,307
You certainly picked
a fine time to do it.

1514
01:15:57,649 --> 01:15:59,809
Now, what's the idea?

1515
01:16:02,953 --> 01:16:05,080
I want to be with you, Loop.

1516
01:16:05,189 --> 01:16:07,248
<i>All airport offiicials
have been asked...</i>

1517
01:16:07,358 --> 01:16:11,818
<i>to report the arrival
of plane NC13843.</i>

1518
01:16:13,963 --> 01:16:16,363
You know, we're really in trouble.

1519
01:16:16,466 --> 01:16:19,765
Loop, you're not awful
mad at me, are you?

1520
01:16:19,869 --> 01:16:22,804
Yes, I'm very mad at you.

1521
01:16:24,873 --> 01:16:27,808
Well, I guess I won't be very long.

1522
01:16:36,885 --> 01:16:38,112
That's right. But be sure...

1523
01:16:38,219 --> 01:16:40,449
and keep me posted
if anything happens.

1524
01:16:40,555 --> 01:16:41,783
Well?

1525
01:16:41,889 --> 01:16:43,823
There isn't any news.

1526
01:16:52,399 --> 01:16:55,266
I blame you two for this.

1527
01:16:55,368 --> 01:16:57,802
If you hadn't been so selfish...

1528
01:16:57,904 --> 01:17:00,805
if you'd just been
a little kinder...

1529
01:17:00,907 --> 01:17:03,397
that child would
never have left here.

1530
01:17:03,509 --> 01:17:06,774
You people have everything
to make life worthwhile-

1531
01:17:06,879 --> 01:17:09,780
youth and health and money.

1532
01:17:09,882 --> 01:17:12,783
And yet you were too mean
and too narrow to share it...

1533
01:17:12,885 --> 01:17:14,977
with a little child
who had nothing...

1534
01:17:15,086 --> 01:17:19,216
but who had more
than you'll ever have.

1535
01:17:19,324 --> 01:17:22,725
Well, if anything
happens to her...

1536
01:17:22,827 --> 01:17:26,194
I'm through with you
for good and all.

1537
01:17:38,842 --> 01:17:41,241
Is it always bumpy like this?

1538
01:17:41,344 --> 01:17:44,245
It isn't bumpy till you
hit your head on the top.

1539
01:17:44,347 --> 01:17:46,975
Say, reach in my pocket
and get a stick of gum.

1540
01:17:48,351 --> 01:17:50,251
Isn't this great?

1541
01:17:50,353 --> 01:17:51,752
Uh-huh.

1542
01:17:51,853 --> 01:17:53,218
Give me half.

1543
01:17:56,358 --> 01:17:59,259
Say, what was that
"Lollipop" song?

1544
01:17:59,361 --> 01:18:01,420
Go ahead and sing it.

1545
01:18:01,529 --> 01:18:04,759
<i>? On the good ship Lollipop?</i>

1546
01:18:04,865 --> 01:18:06,765
? It's a sweet trip...?

1547
01:18:08,869 --> 01:18:10,268
?... Bonbons play?

1548
01:18:10,371 --> 01:18:12,839
? On the sunny beach of Peppermint Bay?

1549
01:18:14,275 --> 01:18:16,266
NC13843 calling.

1550
01:18:16,377 --> 01:18:18,674
NC13843 abandoning ship.

1551
01:18:18,778 --> 01:18:20,678
Broken gas line.

1552
01:18:20,780 --> 01:18:23,180
Approximate position-
Can you hear me?

1553
01:18:23,283 --> 01:18:24,682
It's dead.

1554
01:18:24,784 --> 01:18:26,684
What's the matter, Loop?

1555
01:18:26,786 --> 01:18:28,686
Do you love me?

1556
01:18:28,788 --> 01:18:30,186
Of course, Loop.

1557
01:18:30,289 --> 01:18:32,189
How much?

1558
01:18:32,291 --> 01:18:34,225
Oh, you can hug me
tighter than that...

1559
01:18:34,326 --> 01:18:35,759
'cause we're bailin' out.

1560
01:18:38,330 --> 01:18:39,763
Hold tight.

1561
01:19:34,848 --> 01:19:36,748
Are you all right, honey?

1562
01:19:36,850 --> 01:19:38,249
Sure!

1563
01:19:38,352 --> 01:19:40,411
Let's do it again.

1564
01:19:54,867 --> 01:19:56,766
And in conclusion, your honor...

1565
01:19:56,868 --> 01:19:59,393
my client feels that he
is the best qualified...

1566
01:19:59,504 --> 01:20:01,972
and most fit person to have
the custody of this child.

1567
01:20:02,073 --> 01:20:03,472
He therefore prays...

1568
01:20:03,575 --> 01:20:05,509
that you grant him
the right of adoption.

1569
01:20:07,645 --> 01:20:10,374
ZJames Merritt.

1570
01:20:13,217 --> 01:20:14,275
Yes, your honor?

1571
01:20:14,385 --> 01:20:16,114
Aren't you represented by counsel?

1572
01:20:16,220 --> 01:20:17,881
No, sir.

1573
01:20:17,988 --> 01:20:19,785
Well, you've heard all
about the advantages...

1574
01:20:19,890 --> 01:20:21,584
Mr. Smith can give Shirley.

1575
01:20:21,691 --> 01:20:23,591
What have you to offer?

1576
01:20:23,693 --> 01:20:25,126
Not very much.

1577
01:20:25,228 --> 01:20:28,391
I haven't a lot of money,
and I haven't a fine home.

1578
01:20:28,498 --> 01:20:31,433
But I love Shirley,
and I know she loves me.

1579
01:20:31,534 --> 01:20:34,297
I'd do anything
in the world for her.

1580
01:20:37,038 --> 01:20:39,973
Judge: Come on up here
by me, Shirley.

1581
01:20:50,551 --> 01:20:52,985
Up she goes. Yeah.

1582
01:20:55,055 --> 01:20:56,955
Well, looks as though you...

1583
01:20:57,057 --> 01:20:59,456
are a very popular young woman.

1584
01:20:59,559 --> 01:21:03,962
Now, it's my duty to decide
who is going to adopt you...

1585
01:21:04,063 --> 01:21:05,997
but I think you should have
something to say about it...

1586
01:21:06,099 --> 01:21:07,123
don't you?

1587
01:21:07,233 --> 01:21:08,825
Yes, I do.

1588
01:21:08,935 --> 01:21:12,461
Now, uh... which of these people
would you like to live with?

1589
01:21:12,571 --> 01:21:15,972
I'd like to live with him.

1590
01:21:20,212 --> 01:21:22,271
And I'd like to live with him, too.

1591
01:21:27,118 --> 01:21:28,745
And her, too.

1592
01:21:30,588 --> 01:21:32,988
Well, it seems to me that this case...

1593
01:21:33,090 --> 01:21:35,388
can be settled
without attorneys.

1594
01:21:35,493 --> 01:21:38,461
Will all the lawyers
in the courtroom please leave?

1595
01:21:58,747 --> 01:22:01,647
Now, suppose we adjourn
to my chambers.

1596
01:22:01,749 --> 01:22:03,182
Come on, dear.

1597
01:22:06,087 --> 01:22:07,987
Oh, not you, Mr. Merritt...

1598
01:22:08,089 --> 01:22:10,489
nor you, Mr. and Mrs. Smythe.

1599
01:22:10,592 --> 01:22:13,459
I just want to talk to Mr. Smith
and the young lady.

1600
01:22:18,765 --> 01:22:21,097
Mama, do we have to have...

1601
01:22:21,201 --> 01:22:24,102
that old Shirley
living with us again?

1602
01:22:24,204 --> 01:22:25,603
Darling, please, be quiet.

1603
01:22:25,706 --> 01:22:27,070
But, mama, do we?

1604
01:22:27,173 --> 01:22:28,902
Shh! Shh!

1605
01:22:39,017 --> 01:22:40,678
Ha ha ha!

1606
01:22:40,785 --> 01:22:42,912
Ha ha ha!

1607
01:22:44,990 --> 01:22:46,218
Well, Mr. Merritt...

1608
01:22:46,324 --> 01:22:47,882
I've been making
some inquiries...

1609
01:22:47,993 --> 01:22:49,893
and I'm not so sure-

1610
01:22:49,995 --> 01:22:52,428
Would you please
step in here?

1611
01:23:10,013 --> 01:23:13,107
You told Shirley if
she was ever in trouble...

1612
01:23:13,216 --> 01:23:15,116
to send you this ring.

1613
01:23:15,218 --> 01:23:17,583
Well, I want to see
if it's really a magic ring...

1614
01:23:17,686 --> 01:23:20,883
because I'm in trouble.

1615
01:23:20,989 --> 01:23:23,389
You want Shirley...
and I want Shirley.

1616
01:23:23,492 --> 01:23:25,892
If you think hard for a minute...

1617
01:23:25,994 --> 01:23:27,427
can't you figure a way out?

1618
01:23:27,529 --> 01:23:30,224
I don't get you at all.

1619
01:23:31,866 --> 01:23:34,892
Oh, dear. Do I have to propose?

1620
01:23:35,002 --> 01:23:36,765
Well, I did the last time.

1621
01:23:36,871 --> 01:23:38,395
Oh, Loop.

1622
01:23:40,541 --> 01:23:43,941
No. You don't have to propose.

1623
01:23:44,044 --> 01:23:46,945
Maybe all this happened
for a good reason.

1624
01:23:47,047 --> 01:23:48,912
And this time, it'll last forever.

1625
01:23:57,556 --> 01:23:59,956
Well, Uncle Ned, who got Shirley?

1626
01:24:00,059 --> 01:24:01,959
We did.

1627
01:24:02,061 --> 01:24:04,586
Come up and see us sometime.

1628
01:24:08,933 --> 01:24:11,868
Oh, Papa, now we don't have to...

1629
01:24:11,970 --> 01:24:14,336
be nice to Uncle Ned anymore!

